title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put bread crumbs, sausage and cheese in dish.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be mixed the night before, stored in the refrigerator and baked in the morning.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
and
drain;
add remaining ingredients. Mix and
pour into a greased casserole. Top with 1 stack Ritz crackers,
tossed with 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: golden potato soup
directions: Simmer first eight ingredients for 15 minutes and let cool. Melt the margarine and add the flour and milk; cook to thicken. Add the cheese and cook until melted.
Add to cooled vegetables and stir well.
Heat in individual bowls in microwave to serve; do not cover to heat as it will curdle.

title: german apple cake
directions: Cream together milk, margarine, vanilla, sugar and egg.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine topping ingredients and sprinkle on cake before baking.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip(microwave)
directions: Cube Velveeta and pour can of Ro-Tel tomatoes in bowl. Microwave until melted, stirring occasionally.
Add browned, drained ground beef and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in pan; bring to boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper to cool.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all three ingredients together. Add more flour as needed to make consistency.
Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes until golden.

title: pork chops continental
directions: Brown chops, season and place in single layer in pan.
Cover chops with onion and sauerkraut.
Mix beef bouillon and sour cream and pour over sauerkraut.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour in 350° oven. About 10 minutes before serving, sprinkle with crumbs and paprika and finish baking uncovered.
Baste chops a few times after putting the crumbs on top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in La Creme or Cool Whip.
Put in baked pie shell.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken in cream
directions: Cook chicken with a cube of bouillon.
Let come to a boil. Let stand for 15 minutes.
Prepare spinach; drain and spread on the bottom of an 8 x 11-inch dish.
Place chicken evenly.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, cheese and cream of chicken soup.
Spread over chicken evenly. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mamma's bread pudding
directions: Cut up bread.
Soak it in water and milk.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Add butter and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into a loaf pan.

title: mandarin orange jell-o
directions: Make Jell-O using 1 cup hot water and 1 cup juice.
Let it start to jell.
Whip cream.
Whip Jell-O and cream cheese together.
Add whipped cream.
Stir in fruit and chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up cherries; mash cream cheese in (do not drain cherries), then add crushed pineapple, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Then stir and add nuts.

title: apple cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, mix cinnamon and sugar. Unroll crescent rolls and separate into 8 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise to make 16 triangular strips.
Place apple wedge on wide end of each strip; roll up.
Arrange rolls in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Pour orange juice or water into dish but not over rolls.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and apples are tender.

title: noodles
directions: Beat egg, add other ingredients; mix well.
Roll thin on a floured cloth or board.
When dry, roll up and cut.
Slice thin.
I lay them on a towel in the patio until thoroughly dry.
May be stored in pantry or freeze.

title: lamb and lentil stew
directions: Wash and pick over lentils.
Put into deep bowl.
Cover with water.
Soak overnight.
Drain.
Measure liquid and add enough water to make 4 cups.
Add lentils and simmer until tender.

title: peach drop muffins
directions: In bowl, combine bran and milk and let stand five minutes. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and soda, set aside.
Blend mixture just until blended.
Stir in peaches and raisins.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet or spoon batter into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
These contain 155 calories each and no cholesterol.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together first two ingredients.
Stir in eggs, molasses and vinegar.
Sift and add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Form dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet about 12 minutes.
As the ball melts down during baking, the cookie develops the characteristic crinkled surface.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients, except oil, in blender or mixing bowl. Add Crisco oil slowly while blending vigorously with the blender or egg beater.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Use
rubber
gloves when you chop jalapeno pepper.
Mix all ingredients
except
cheese.
Pour	1/2
batter
into hot greased iron skillet.
Sprinkle half of grated cheese on top. Pour remaining
batter
and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Save stems for other use.
Wipe caps with paper towel.
Put into jar.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Heat just to boiling point.
Pour over mushrooms, cool.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 days.
Shake twice a day.
When serving, drain and serve with toothpicks.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan and cook until all is mixed well.

title: cookie salad
directions: Stir buttermilk into pudding; fold in Cool Whip.
Add drained fruit.
Fold in 2/3 of crushed cookies.
Sprinkle remaining crushed cookies on top.

title: banana-date nut bread
directions: About 2 hours before serving or day ahead:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, with fork, mix first 5 ingredients.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor-fashion, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in bananas, dates, walnuts and eggs just until blended; spread batter evenly in pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes along bottom and
sides of 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix ham, broccoli, 1/2 onions, 1/2 cheese, soup, milk and seasoning. Pour over potatoes.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remainder of cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer, uncovered.
Remove from oven and let rest 5 minutes before serving.

title: chess cake
directions: Cream this together and spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: honey barbecued chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken; blend remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken into sauce and lay in 9 x 13-inch pan, lined with foil. Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt together
1 1/2 cubes margarine and peanut butter. Stir in the graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar; mix well and pat into
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together the additional margarine and the
chocolate chips.
Spread into an even layer over the crumb
mixture.
Cool
and cut into squares.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen squares.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: In large saucepan, brown sausage; drain.
Remove half of sausage; set aside.
Stir tomato sauce, paste, water and brown sugar into sausage; simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, combine remaining sausage, Ricotta cheese, 2 cups Mozzarella, egg and parsley.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, pour 1/3 spaghetti sauce mixture.
Stuff manicotti noodles with Ricotta mixture and place on top of sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over filled noodles, top with remaining Mozzarella and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening and sugar and set.
Let cool a bit, then add dry yeast, water and 1/2 flour.
Add beaten eggs and beat well.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Then mix through and let rise.
Punch down dough, then make balls.
Then let balls rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes on lower rack.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine brownie mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl; stir with spoon until well blended, or 50 strokes.
Stir in white chocolate. Spread in pan.
Sprinkle top with almonds.
Bake for 25 to 28 minutes, or until set.
Cool completely on wire rack; cut into bars.
Makes 4 dozen small or 2 dozen large brownies.
tags: brownies plus milk chocolate chunks mix

title: chuck wagon roast and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown roast in oil.
Place in baking dish.
Add flour to drippings in skillet and cook and stir until browned.
Add buttermilk, water, bouillon, thyme and pepper.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves and mixture thickens.
Place vegetables and onions around the roast, then add sauce over meat.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: pudding torte
directions: Mix crackers and oleo together.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes. Mix pudding, ice cream and milk together.
Spoon over crust. Sprinkle crushed Heath bars over top.
Refrigerate.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix rice with sugar, marshmallows, pineapple, apple, pecans, raisins and peaches.
Just before serving, add banana slices and fold in whipped cream.
Top with coconut.
Garnish with cherries.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 muffin cup pan or line with paper baking cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and pumpkin, adding eggs one at a time.
Sift together the rest of the ingredients.
Add alternately to pumpkin mixture with 2/3 cup water, starting and ending with flour mixture.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla. Grease and flour 2 large or 3 small loaf pans.
Fill half full. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Check in 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in casserole dish 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in small casserole pan. Bake at 400 degrees till brown, about 30 minutes.

title: make ahead bran muffins
directions: Mix buttermilk and soda, then add oil, molasses and eggs. Stir, then add dry ingredients, stirring well.
Store in refrigerator.
Bake in 375° oven about 20 minutes or until done. Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Muffin pans should be greased.
Makes 48 good-sized muffins.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix and combine all of the above and set aside for 15 minutes.

title: grandma's nut loaf
directions: Mix dates, raisins, hot water and soda; soak for 3 hours or until cool.
Mix eggs, brown sugar, oleo, flour, vanilla and nuts; add to raisin mixture.
Bake in 2 to 3 loaf bread pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brown sugar no-bake cookies
directions: Boil milk, butter and brown sugar together for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.	Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.

title: ginney's greek sauce
directions: Cook meat and spices for 1/2 hour, stirring often. Add tomato paste and 3 to 4 cups water. Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water in a large bowl; stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Let cool.
Add lemon extract, oil and cake mix, blending well.
Beat in eggs.

title: peaches "n" cream pie
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Beat all ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Pour in pie pan and push up along sides.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over split toasted hamburger buns.

title: pork chop casserole 1
directions: Season pork chops with salt, pepper, and worcestershire sauce. Brown pork chops in a skillet.
Remove pork chops and set aside.

Drain off any excess amounts of grease. Combine rice, water, worcestershire to taste, and bouillon cubes in skillet. Stir and mix well. Pour mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Place pork chops on top. Top pork chops with onion rings and peppers as desired.
Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 11 x 13-inch casserole dish. Melt 1 stick of butter.
Cover the top with cracker crumbs. Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: First Layer:
Mix pecans (chopped fine), flour and melted margarine.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Cook margarine, cocoa, sugar and milk until bubbles form around sides.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop onto waxed paper; cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Prepare fruit; stir in vanilla pudding.
This will thicken the salad.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.
Serves 6.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs, then blend in other ingredients except marshmallows.
Grease and flour oblong pan and cook 30 minutes on 300°.
Remove and spread marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until marshmallows melt.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add boiling water.
Add sugar, pineapple juice, pineapple, lemon juice and salt; mix well (stir).
Put in refrigerator and leave until partly jelled (slimy like beef broth).

title: hummus dip
directions: Place drained beans in blender.
Add all other ingredients, then add enough water to almost cover beans.
Blend until smooth. Pour into serving dish.
Pour very thin layer of olive oil on top; sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with pita bread.

title: sugar-free peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on packages.
Add peanut butter and pour directly into pie shell.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: crispy chicken sandwich
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well. Spread evenly on 10 slices of bread.
Top with the remaining 10 slices. Wrap individually in freezer wrap and freeze.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix mashed sweet potatoes, eggs, sugar, and oleo. Pour in a buttered 9 x 12 casserole dish. Mix brown sugar, flour, oleo, and pecans for topping. Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: krumkaker
directions: Bake on medium heat, use a small bowl in mixing.
Bake in krum kake iron.
Use 1 tablespoon butter or less, depending on size you wish.
Roll on cone stick.
Put iron on burner when starting to make batter.

title: holiday stuffing
directions: Cook sausage.
Cook onion, celery and garlic until celery is soft.
Mix with dry stuffing.
Add chicken broth to moisten.
Add beaten eggs.
Stuff bird.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off excess grease.
In skillet or saucepan, mix all ingredients (except buns) and stir well.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: peanut butter delight(fudge)
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 3 minutes (after it starts boiling).
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal.
Stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat well, quickly.
It sets up fast.
Drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls or put into pan and cut into bars.

title: grandma richards' raisin filled cookies
directions: In a medium sized saucepan, combine the raisins and just enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together, then add to raisins.
Boil until slightly thickened, about 1 minute.
Allow mixture to cool completely before making cookies.

title: jam kolaches
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add flour, mixing well.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds with a 2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spoon 1/4 teaspoon jam on each cookie; fold in opposite sides, slightly overlapping edges.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over and stir corn flakes.
Spoon out onto wax paper. Cool.

title: swiss meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given.
Press into one large greased loaf pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: from scratch cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together into large mixing bowl.
Add oil and vanilla to milk and pour into bowl with other ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes on medium.
Add unbeaten eggs and beat 2 minutes longer.
Pour into 2 greased 8 or 9-inch layer pans.
Bake in 375° oven about 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
When cool, ice with Fluffy Frosting.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Roll into balls and put on cookie sheet.
Freeze for 1 hour.
After mix is frozen, melt wax on low heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Keep on low heat while using toothpick to dip balls into chocolate and replace on cookie sheet.
Freeze or refrigerate.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook pepper,
garlic
and onion in butter until tender. Add remaining
ingredients, except chicken.
Cook until thick. Add chicken and heat.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Slice
potatoes
and
onions
into
baking
dish.
Pour drained
peas
and carrots across layered potatoes and onions, then pour
can
of corn with its juice across that layer of vegetables.
Sprinkle ground beef across and top with 1 can of tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: homemade "shake 'n make" oven frying mix for chicken
directions: Combine the preceding listed ingredients in a tightly covered, moisture-proof container.
Stir until well mixed.
Use about 1 tablespoon of the mixture per serving of chicken parts.
Moisten chicken in tomato juice, skim milk, white wine, lemon juice or water before shaking with crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken pieces on a rack, skin side up, and allow to dry 15 or 20 minutes while oven preheats.

title: turnip green casserole
directions: Mix everything together except cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
During last 5 minutes, sprinkle cheese on top.
May double recipe.
Freezes well.

title: corn flake treats
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and margarine for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in corn flakes and press into oblong pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve liquid.
Mix cheese, sugar and flour.
Add pineapple.
Add small amount of liquid as needed.
Top with crushed cheese crackers or Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: papoose pie
directions: Cook pie shell.
Mix together cream cheese and Cool Whip. Line pie shell with sliced bananas.
Pour cream cheese and Cool Whip over bananas.
Pour pie filling over cream cheese mixture.

title: asparagus and mushrooms(serves 4)
directions: Cook asparagus 5 minutes; drain.
Arrange asparagus and mushrooms in bottom of shallow dish. Mix other ingredients well; pour over asparagus.
Serve chilled.

title: coconut buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake toat 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet and cool in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate candy coating and dip balls.

title: southern cannon balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into walnut size balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: reduced calorie white cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat egg whites gradually adding 1/4 cup sugar until stiff peaks form.
Combine oil, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add liquids.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed; add remaining milk and beat another minute.
Carefully fold egg whites into cake batter. Divide batter into 2 layer cake pans coated with cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 24 servings; 113 calories per serving.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off excess grease.
Add barbecue sauce, instant onion and garlic powder; mix well.
Flatten each biscuit and press into muffin tin.
Spoon beef mixture into center of each biscuit cup, then top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meatballs in sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and shape into meatballs. Heat together the soup and water. Drop meatballs into gravy and simmer for 1 hour.

title: best banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with 2 cups cold milk.
Fold in 8 ounces sour cream and 1 cup Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Mix
all together and let rise until doubled.
Dump out on floured
paper
and knead until fluffy.
Roll out like pie crust. Spread
melted margarine on dough.	Then mix sugar and cinnamon and
sprinkle over dough.
Roll up and cut into buns about 1/2-inch
thick.
Put
in
greased pan, let rise again. Bake
at about
Top with icing made from confectioners sugar and a little margarine while hot.

title: modern grated sweet potato pudding
directions: (Be sure to place ingredients in blender container in order listed.)
Place eggs and milk in blender.
Peel potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Add to eggs and milk, along with sugar, salt and 1/2 stick of margarine.
Blend about 15 to 20 seconds or until potatoes have blended well.
The other 1/2 stick of margarine should be melting in a casserole dish.
Pour potato mixture into buttered casserole.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until golden brown.
Serve warm as a side dish or as a dessert with light or whipped cream.

title: ambrosia
directions: Dissolve warm gelatin in small amount of 7-Up; mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potatoes until soft; mash while warm.
Add sugar, coconut and flavoring.
Shape to desired size.
Can be dipped in chocolate.

title: swiss steak
directions: Take steak pieces that have been salted, peppered and floured and brown in skillet with oil.
Add ingredients to browned steak. Add water to cover all pieces of meat.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: mustard slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shred vegetables.
Boil 20 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: salmon casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, put drained salmon.
"Smash" with a fork to crush any bones (they are very soft).
Mix in soup and half of the cheese, then add the rice.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Cut and drain fruit.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and curry powder.
Add oleo to fruit and sugar mixture. Mix fruit lightly. Turn into buttered casserole. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: minnesota maple cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix or sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture in three parts, alternating with maple syrup and milk.
Spread batter in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: cold cut bread
directions: Beat the egg.
Chop cold cuts.
Put into egg and mix.
Spread dough on greased baking pan.
Place cold cuts down the center of the dough.
Fold ends of dough over each other to form bread. Pinch all ends to prevent breakage.
Bake in 350° oven until it is golden.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients; heat until bubbly.
Put into a 2-quart casserole. Cut biscuits in halves to form 20 half-circles.
Place, cut sides down, around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese (biscuits). Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.

title: mexican pepper casserole
directions: In a saute pan, heat oil and butter; add onions, garlic, salt and spices (except paprika) and saute until onions are translucent.
Lower heat; add peppers and saute for 10 minutes. Sprinkle in flour, mixing well, and saute until liquid is absorbed; remove from heat.
Butter a deep casserole dish; place one-half of mixture in dish and top with one-half of the cheese. Repeat.
Mix eggs and sour cream together and pour over peppers and cheese mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Step 1.
Peel onions; cut off and discard root ends.
Using a large knife, slice onions thinly.
In a 4 qt. saucepan, over medium high heat, melt butter.
Add onions and ground black pepper to butter.

title: 6 week pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut off ends. Put whole cucumbers in glass jars. Cover with vinegar; add salt, pickling spice and alum. Cover jar and set aside for 5 weeks.

title: new england injun' puddin'
directions: Heat 2 cups of milk.
Add molasses, sugar, corn meal, salt, spices and butter.
Cook 20 minutes or until the mixture thickens. Pour into baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Do not stir. Bake at 300°.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or hard sauce.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix the syrup, molasses, sugar, vinegar, salt and margarine in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stirring constantly, bring the mixture to a boil over a medium heat.
Boil gently until the mixture reaches the hard crack stage (290° on a candy thermometer).
Add the soda and mix well.
Pour the foamy mixture over 6 to 8 cups of popped popcorn.
Stir well as you pour the mixture on the corn.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and cool.
Mix onion, lettuce, tomato, cheese, beans and cooled hamburger.
Add Doritos and dressing just before serving.

title: mom's poorhouse bread
directions: In a large bowl, pour in 4 cups lukewarm water.
Sprinkle in yeast, sugar and salt.
Let sit 15 minutes.
Add oil and eggs. Stir.
Add flour to make stiff.
Knead well.
Lightly oil top and bottom of dough.
Let rise until double in size.
Work down and put in pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. (Loaves for 1 hour and rolls for 30 to 35 minutes.)

title: island chicken marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over chicken and marinate for 4 hours.
Turn at least once in marinade.
Chicken may be broiled, baked or charcoal broiled.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges.
Arrange potatoes, peel side down, in shallow pan.
Mix ingredients and brush on potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown, brushing occasionally with oil mixture.

title: barbara's coffee cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in bowl and add margarine, cutting together with knife as for pastry.
Reserve 3/4 cup of mixture for topping.
To remainder of mixture, add baking powder, evaporated milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix together well. Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first three ingredients together over medium heat until it thickens and looks clear.
While still hot, add jello.
When this mixture cools, fold in berries.
Put in two cooked 9-inch pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: lemon dessert
directions: First Layer:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and nuts until crumbly.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill dip for 2 to 3 hours prior to serving.
Serve with your choice of tortilla chips.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute onion, garlic, chiles, salt, pepper, chili powder and cumin in margarine.
Cook chicken; shred meat with fingers very fine.
Mix in the sauteed mixture.
You may want to add some chicken broth.
Season to taste.
Roll in flour tortillas and fry. Serve with taco sauce or sour cream.

title: fattigman(crisp pastry cookie)
directions: Beat together egg yolks and salt until thick and light.
Beat in light cream, sugar and butter.
Sift together flour and nutmeg. Add to egg yolk mixture with lemon peel, mixing well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out 1/4 of dough at a time.
Keep remaining dough chilled.
Roll to 1/16-inch thick and cut in strips about 1 1/2-inch wide with sharp knife.
Cut diagonally at 4-inch intervals.
Make 1-inch slits lengthwise in center of each piece. Slip one end through slit.
Fry a few at a time in deep, hot oil at 350° for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden.
Remove from oil with slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: puffy omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and water until stiff, not dry.
Combine egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Beat until thick. Gently fold yolk mixture into whites.

title: russian tea
directions: Use 3 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup boiling water.
This makes 1 quart dry mixture.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Chill dough and drop by teaspoonfuls onto a baking sheet or roll into a ball the size of a walnut.
Flatten with a small glass bottom dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken-crescent roll casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
When cool, pick off of bone; break into pieces.
Roll up chicken into crescent rolls and put in a baking dish.
What chicken is left over, place it all around baking dish and over crescent rolls.
Mix cream of chicken soup and milk (or I use chicken broth).
Pour over crescent rolls. Bake at 350° until rolls are golden brown.
Top with cheese, if you like, and bake.
(I leave cheese off.)

title: ma's green beans
directions: In large saucepan, brown bacon and onions together in pan. Pour green beans in pan and cook down almost dry.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Butter a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Combine milk and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Heat until a thin film appears on surface.
Stir until blended.
Prepare and turn into a large bowl 3 cups bread crumbs.
Mix chopped walnuts.
Add chocolate mixture gradually to bread crumbs, mixing thoroughly with a fork. Mix together eggs, brown sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour egg mixture over bread crumb mixture.
Toss with fork to blend well.
Turn into prepared casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Mix both packages of jello with boiling water. Stir until dissolved. Add juice drained from pineapple and condensed milk. Mix well. Add mayonnaise, drained pineapple, cottage cheese and chopped pecans. Mix well and chill until firmly set.

title: shrimp curry with coconut milk
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add onion and brown.
Add all the spices and saute for 2 minutes.
Add shrimp and saute 1/2 minute. Add coconut milk (strained) and 1/4 cup shredded coconut that is leftover after straining.
Cover and cook on medium heat until the gravy thickens.
Serve over plain rice or polao.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk gradually. Mix well. Add salt and baking powder. Sift with flour and salt. Add margarine, vanilla and coconut. Pour into 2 (8-inch) pie pans, lightly greased. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set. Makes its own crust.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: jason's baked beans
directions: Mix onion soup mix with juice from 3 cans of pinto beans. Heat 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: beef and cabbage taco casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, toss together potatoes, the 1/2 cup cheese, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/8 teaspoon onion salt.
Press into bottom and sides of greased 1-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: one skillet meal
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Pour in vegetables and juice, tomato sauce and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and bring to a boil. Arrange biscuits on top and cover tightly.
Let simmer on stove top for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream salmon loaf
directions: Remove any fine bones from salmon; drain liquid.
Crush corn flakes into fine crumbs.
Combine all ingredients together.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake in a loaf pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling. Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
While cooling, soften the cream cheese.
Mix with sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Beat mixture together.
When jello is partially set, top with cream cheese mixture.
Chill until set.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place chicken on bottom of greased casserole dish.
Put broccoli on top.
Mix other ingredients and pour over top.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Continue boiling for 1 1/2 minutes.
After mixture has reached a full rolling boil, remove from heat.
Blend together the oatmeal, chopped nuts, vanilla and peanut butter with first mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: low-fat unfried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals, then slice lengthwise into matchsticks.
Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of spray. Combine the egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl. Add the potatoes and mix to coat.
Pour the coated potatoes onto the pan and spread into a single layer. Place the baking sheet on the bottom shelf of the oven and cook 45 minutes, turning every 8 minutes. Serve immediately.
Contains 0.5 grams of fat and 291 calories per serving. Serves 4.

title: angel meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and salt. Add sugar, gradually beating after each addition. The secret is in beating in the sugar. Grease 9-inch dish. Spread mixture evenly in dish. Have oven heated to 450°. Turn off heat. Put dish in oven overnight. Top with whipped cream, bananas and strawberries. Yum!

title: holiday cherry squares
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, combine corn flake crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press down firmly with back of spoon.
Sprinkle marshmallows, coconut and cherries in layers evenly over crumbs. Pour milk evenly over top.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over all, pressing lightly into mixture.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
Refrigerate before cutting into 1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: dill chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter in skillet until light brown, about 5 minutes on each side.
Mix wine, lemon juice, salt and dill weed and pour over chicken.
Place lemon slices on top and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until chicken is done.
Remove chicken; heat juice until boiling and half remains.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle onions over top.

title: candied fruit bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine eggs, milk and salad oil.
Add to flour mixture, beating well. Stir in 1 cup candied fruit and 1/2 cup nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all together and spread in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a large oblong casserole dish.
Pour jar of salsa over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top of salsa and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bow tie pasta with sausage, tomatoes and cream
directions: Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add sausage and pepper flakes and cook for 7 minutes, breaking up sausage while doing so.
Add onion and garlic and cook 7 more minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and cream and simmer over low heat for about 4 minutes.

title: party ham casserole
directions: Combine in saucepan soup and milk.
Add onion, mustard and sour cream; stir to combine well.
In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half of cooked noodles, ham slivers and sauce; repeat.
Toss bread crumbs with butter.
Sprinkle over casserole. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix with electric mixer.
Pour into 2 or 3 prepared 9-inch pans.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 25 minutes, or until brown.
Cool thoroughly.

title: manicotti
directions: Drain manicotti and place on foil in single layer to dry. Melt butter; add sauce and garlic powder.
Pour some sauce on bottom of baking dish.
Mix salt, cottage cheese, bread crumbs, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Stuff pasta.
Place in baking dish on top of sauce.
Spoon remaining sauce over top. Sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella cheese over sauce.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix milk, sugar and egg yolks.
Cook over low heat over water, stirring constantly until thickened; cool.
Cream together butter, confectioners sugar and cooled chocolate.
Blend with first mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold chocolate mixture into egg whites.
Blend well.
Sprinkle half of crumbs into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour mixture on top of crumbs.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Chill overnight.
May be served with Cool Whip.

title: tender lovin lemony chicken
directions: Empty contents of Shake 'N Bake envelope into shaker bag.
Add lemon peel.
Combine juice and water in small bowl.
Moisten chicken with juice mixture.
Coat chicken.

title: kate's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Pull off bone. Mix and heat soup, broth, sour cream and poppy seed.
Put chicken in casserole and pour soup mixture over.
Put crackers and margarine on top.
Cook at 325° until bubbly for 30 minutes.

title: creole pralines
directions: Put all ingredients, except the pecans, in a 3-quart saucepan and cook for about 20 minutes at medium temperature.
After boiling, stir occasionally.
Add the pecans and cook the mixture until the liquid forms a soft ball when a little is dropped into cold water.
Stir well and then drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Place in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Roll small balls, dip into sesame seeds and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until light golden brown on bottom of cookie.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare taco filling with ground beef and taco sauce mix. Melt cheese with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix shredded lettuce, tomatoes, meat and 1/4 of the corn chips in a salad bowl.
Pour cheese mixture over and top with remaining corn chips.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Allow hash browns to partially thaw and mix all of the ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put in a large casserole dish and top with 2 cups crushed cornflakes mixed with 1/2 cup margarine. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Beat well.
Mix crushed wafers and 1/2 cup milk.
Add coconut and nuts.
Line tube pan with 2 layers of wax paper and pour in mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Cook until thick on low heat; add 1/2 cup of canned milk, 2 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla and continue to cook until it thickens.
Pour while hot on ice cream.

title: crab quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 425° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread cheese in bottom of pie shell.
Mix together remaining ingredients and spread over cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then lower heat to 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Great for breakfast or dinner.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a 9x13-inch casserole dish.

title: strawberry frozen jam
directions: Combine all ingredients. Let stand 1/2 hour. Stir occasionally. Put into containers and store in freezer. Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix sugar a little at a time with Hershey bars and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat into eggs the white sugar and brown sugar.
Add oil and vanilla.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir in grated zucchini and nuts.
Bake in 2 or 3 small greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut meat into 1/4 to 1/2-inch strips.
Marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain strips on paper.
Pat excess off.
Put oven on lowest heat.
Put meat on wire rack; dry for 10 hours.

title: quick 'n easy refrigerator fudge
directions: Place chips in top of double boiler over hot water; stir frequently and melt.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan lined with waxed paper. Refrigerate until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off waxed paper and cut as desired.
Yield:
Approximately 2 pounds.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in 4 cups water.
Add margarine, cheese, salt and eggs.
Pour into ungreased dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in pineapple with juice; add vanilla and milk.
Fold in bread cubes. Put into buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with mixture of brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Roll in one inch diameter logs. Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill well.
Beat egg, salt, sugar and butter until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Use miniature nonstick muffin pans (makes 24).
Slice chilled dough stick into 1/4 inch slices. Press into muffin cups.
Add filling by teaspoon.
Sprinkle in the nuts.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Cut shortening until particles are like coarse cornbread.
Add soda to buttermilk and stir into flour mixture.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board.
Roll out and cut with floured cutter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Dream Whip and pudding (after preparing) together in a large bowl.
Stir until it becomes thick.
Drain all fruit, then pour in with Dream Whip and pudding.
Add marshmallows and nuts. Stir until mixed well.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh grape pie
directions: Mix sugar and flavor together.
Cut grapes in half; take seeds out.
Put a little flour mixture in bottom of raw crust.
Mix the rest of mixture in with grapes.
Put in raw pie shell.
Put top crust on.
Slit top crust.
Bake in moderate oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili con carne with tomatoes
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and green pepper in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients, except beans.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally or cook uncovered 45 minutes.
Stir in beans last.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix cooked rice, sour cream, green chilies and seasonings.
Place half the mixture in a greased baking dish.
Top with a layer of shredded cheese. Repeat layers; top with dots of butter.
Bake for 30 minutes or until heated throughout.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar and oil.
Mix all together and let stand overnight (the longer it stands the better it is).

title: green's salad
directions: Mix pudding and undrained pineapple together.
Mix marshmallows and Cool Whip together.
Put in icebox for 1 hour. Serve.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except candy in large mixer bowl.
Mix on low speed until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a candy Kiss. Press down firmly so cookies crack around edge.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: peanut butter fudge pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add peanut butter; beat until fluffy.
Add ice cream.
Pour into prepared crusts.
Marble fudge topping into pie and then decorate top with remaining chocolate.
Freeze.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add chilies, soup and milk; mix well.
Dip one tortilla into hot cooking oil, just long enough to make limp and place into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Add 2 generous tablespoons of chicken soup mixture and a small amount of cheese.
Roll enchilada style.
Repeat process until all tortillas are used, then pour remaining soup mixture over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: martha craver's fluffy gingerbread
directions: Cream the butter with sifted brown sugar.
Add the eggs and molasses.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Add boiling water last.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and eggs into pudding mix in saucepan. Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Pour into serving bowl and chill about 1 hour.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and honey.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add milk to eggs and to creamed mixture; beat thoroughly. Sift together flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture. Chop raisins and figs and add, then add spices as desired.
Bake at 375° in tube pan for about 30 minutes.

title: garlic spareribs(china)
directions: Combine juice, vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and garlic in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil over low heat for 30 minutes. While sauce is cooking, place ribs in a large saucepan with diced onion and cover with water, boil over low heat for 15 minutes. Remove from saucepan and place in baking dish. When sauce is done, pour over ribs. Marinate for 8-12 hours in refrigerator, then drain off sauce. Bake ribs in covered dish on top oven rack at 400 for 1 1/2 hours. Remove lid and bake an additional 10 minutes. Serve.

title: goulash
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes, then roll in flour.
Brown on low temperature in fat.
Chop onion fine.
Chop garlic.
Cut carrots into 2-inch lengths.
Add all other ingredients together and pour over the browned beef.
Cover and cook at very low heat for 1 1/4 hours.
Add carrots the last 30 minutes of cooking.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Mix cornbread, as directed, in large casserole dish. Brown and drain ground beef. Stir in taco seasoning. Add to casserole dish. Add beans (undrained) and creamed corn. Top with cheese. Bake, covered, or, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
(Also good with green peppers and chopped stewed tomatoes.)

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch square pan.
Drain fruit and pour liquid in pan and mix with butter.
Spread fruit over bottom of pan.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add egg and mix well.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add water and sugar to chopped cranberries and boil 5 minutes. Pour this over Jell-O and marshmallows until dissolved.
Cool and add nuts, celery and apples.
Place in refrigerator.
Keeps for days.
Keep a couple of days before serving.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, molasses and egg until fluffy. Sift together flour, soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves; stir into molasses mixture.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine flour, margarine and nuts until crumbly.
Pat mixture into bottom of an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: chocolate pecan candy
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in saucepan and cook on high to a rolling boil that cannot be stirred down.
Cook 90 seconds longer, unstirred.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Cool slightly in a sink of cold water.
Stir in 1 cup of chopped pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish and let cool.

title: honey crunch nut bars
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Put butter, honey, brown sugar and cinnamon into a 3-quart saucepan.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat, then boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Add noodles and gently stir (fold) until coated.
Stir in nuts.
Scrape mixture into prepared pan.
Cover with waxed paper and press into an even layer.
Remove paper; let stand at least 1 hour before cutting bars with a large heavy knife.

title: meat balls in a flash
directions: Mix ingredients with small amount of soup.
Put rest of soup in pot with enough water to cover meat balls and cook until done.

title: cold ketchup
directions: Grind together the tomatoes, green and red peppers, onions and celery.
Add 1/2 c. salt.
Pour into a bag and drain until no liquid comes out.
Add
vinegar and sugar. Warm together until sugar dissolves.
Add celery seed and mustard seed.
Can. No cooking and no need to process. Will keep on shelf.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Spread rice in buttered, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange broccoli over rice.
Top with chicken.
Blend soup, sour cream, milk, lemon juice and half of cheese.
Add salt and pepper. Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: icelandic coconut and raisin cakes
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and coconut.
Add margarine and eggs.
Mix well.
Add cream of tartar and raisins.
Mix well. Form into balls and roll in coconut.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: mushroom a'la lyonnaise
directions: Heat butter.
When foam subsides, add onion and stir well. Add mushrooms and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook until mushrooms are lightly browned on all sides.
Remove and spoon into the center of the spinach ring.
Sprinkle mushrooms with lemon juice and parsley.
Pour butter in which mushrooms were cooked over the top.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Fold in pistachio pudding mix with thawed Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, including juice.
Add 1/2 of marshmallows and mix well. Spread remaining marshmallows on top.
Let set in fridge for at least 1/2 hour before serving.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 2.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In saucepan melt butter.
Blend in flour and cheese.
Add milk slowly.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Place broccoli in 1 qt. dish.
Pour sauce over top with crackers.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: This is always made without measuring, so amounts are very approximate.

title: cheese and beef upside-down cornbread
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add beef and onions.
Cook until beef is lightly browned.
Stir in flour; add tomato paste, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and olives.
Spread evenly over the bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool for 15 minutes, then poke holes down through cake with fork.

title: pumpkin-spice pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients with hand beater until smooth.
For each pancake pour scant 1/4 cup batter onto hot griddle.
(Grease griddle if necessary.)
Cook until pancakes are dry around edges. Turn.
Cook other side until golden brown.
Makes about 13 pancakes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine salt with flour, pound seasoned flour into steak with a meat mallet.
Place fat in skillet on medium heat.
Brown well on both sides.
After browning, remove from skillet.
Saute onion and peppers in remaining fat.
Add water and tomato juice, thicken slightly with flour and water paste.
Return steak to gravy, cover skillet and bake in oven on low heat until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat together oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add zucchini and dry ingredients.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nut.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken-vegetable soup
directions: Combine water, bouillon granules, tomatoes, onion, basil, paprika, garlic and salt in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; cover. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add carrots; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, zucchini, chicken and wine; simmer, uncovered, 8 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yield:
7 cups (about 90 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: cherry surprise cookies
directions: Combine the ingredients; mix well.
Chill the dough 1 hour. Take 1 teaspoon of dough and wrap around a candied cherry.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Keep cool.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and chill overnight.

title: mrs. fair's salmon salad
directions: Combine ingredients and use to "dress" slaw.
Reduce quantities for a small family.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to egg and sugar mixture.
Stir in M&M's. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: picnic turnovers
directions: Combine meat, mayonnaise, mustard, onion juice and pickle; mix well.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until consistency of meal.
Add milk until a soft dough is formed. Roll lightly on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 4-inch squares.
Brush squares with melted butter.
Place triangle of cheese on half of square.
Put 1 tablespoon meat mixture on cheese and fold over other half of dough to form triangle.
Press edges together.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 10.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix until smooth.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.

title: kraut
directions: Add salt to cabbage. Let set 14 days in crock covered with a plate. After fermented, pack in jars. Bring water to boil in water bath canner to seal.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Mix above ingredients, except chicken, chicken broth and soup. Add enough chicken
broth to moisten.
Add undiluted soup.

title: soft tea cakes
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix and drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° approximately 8 minutes.
Cool and store in tightly covered container.

title: breakfast casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Layer in casserole bread, ham and cheese.
Sprinkle flour, mustard and butter.
Pour over milk and eggs.
Chill about 4 hours or overnight.
May be frozen.!

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix strawberries and rhubarb with 1 1/2 cups sugar and the tapioca; let stand while making pastry.
Divide pastry in half.
On lightly floured surface roll out one portion 1 1/2 inches larger than inverted 9-inch pie plate.
Fit into pie pan and trim crust even with edge.
Fill with fruit mixture.
Roll out remaining pastry; lift onto pie.
Trim crust 1/2 inch beyond edge of pie pan. Fold top crust under bottom crust; seal together to make a standing rim and flute edge.
Cut vents in top crust.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 400° oven 60 to 70 minutes or until filling bubbles in the center.
After 30 minutes of baking, check pie occasionally and cover edges with foil, if necessary, to prevent browning.
If pie begins to bubble over, place foil beneath pie plate.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sweet potato casserole #1
directions: Peel, boil and mash sweet potatoes.
Add softened butter, eggs and sherry.
Whip mixture until fluffy.
Add seasonings and fold in 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Place in rectangular casserole dish. Pour melted butter over top and sprinkle with remaining pecans. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Top generously with marshmallows and broil until top is brown.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and peanut butter and beat well.
Combine oats, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets; remove to wire racks.
Yield: 9 dozen.

title: estelle's "goo-losh"
directions: Put on large pan of water.
Add 1 teaspoon vegetable oil.
When it starts to boil, add 1 package curley macaroni, stirring occasionally.
When done, drain well.
Brown hamburger meat, 1 medium bell pepper and 1 medium onion (chopped).
Let simmer until done in covered pan.
When done, add garlic salt and black pepper to suit taste.
Now add 2 small cans tomato paste and 1 can small tomatoes (No. 2 can).
Let simmer until it is done, then pour over macaroni and mix well.
Makes servings for 4.

title: s'mores
directions: Place graham crackers on an oven-proof plate.
Top with milk chocolate bar and heat briefly under broiler or in a hot oven. Cut marshmallows in half and place over melted chocolate bar. Broil marshmallows until golden brown.
Drizzle chocolate syrup randomly over marshmallow and serve immediately.

title: shrimp in lobster sauce
directions: Put 2 tablespoons of oil in a hot skillet.
Combine pork, celery, garlic and seasonings; cook about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and saute until pink (5 to 8 minutes).
Add chicken stock and cook 10 minutes.
Thicken with blended cornstarch, water and soy sauce, stirring.
Add beaten egg to bubbling mixture in slow steady stream.
Top with sliced scallions.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat undiluted soup to boiling.
Add gelatine and let cool.
Add cream cheese and beat with mixer until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into two small or one large mold (greased).
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet cream biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients until dough forms.
Turn onto surface well dusted with baking mix.
Gently roll to coat; shape into ball. Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter dipped in baking mix.
Bake on greased cookie sheet until golden, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen biscuits.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread raise; place dough on greased cookie sheet.
Pat it out long and thin.
Arrange ham on top and center, then pepperoni on top.
Sprinkle half of spices.
Next, Provolone, then Mozzarella.
Sprinkle rest of spices.
Moisten edges of dough with water.
Bring edges up over meat and cheese to form loaf.
Pinch closed.
Turn over and cover with butter.
Sprinkle with cornmeal. Bake in 375° oven 20 to 22 minutes.
Heat jar spaghetti sauce while cooking.
Cut servings and pour sauce on each serving.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and add the flour. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Flour kneading board lightly and roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place in baking dish and allow to rise for 2 hours. Before baking, brush tops with melted butter. Bake at 450° for approximately 13 to 14 minutes. Can be baked immediately, but better if you let them rise. Very easy and very good.

title: pumpkinetts
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin bake
directions: Marinate pork tenderloin in all ingredients except bacon. Place bacon slices on top of pork.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice. Blend until smooth. Fold in marshmallow cream. Chill before serving. Serve with strawberries, pineapple chunks, kiwi, grapes, etc.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add Crisco, buttermilk and bananas; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pan.
Bake 2 (9-inch) layer pans for 35 minutes, a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan for 45 to 50 minutes and a Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Combine whipped topping and condensed milk; stir into chilled pudding.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with cookies, banana slices and filling.
Repeat, ending with crushed cookies. Makes 16 servings.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, preheat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet saute beef and onion until onion is tender, about 10 minutes.

title: meat pastry
directions: Brown beef and then drain fat.
Salt and pepper to taste. Melt margarine and put aside.
Divide fillo package in half. Grease 13 x 9-inch pan and place first fillo sheet in pan and brush on margarine.
Repeat until the first half is finished and then spread the beef mixture evenly.
Repeat second half of fillo dough as done in the first half over the beef mixture.
Cut into 3 to 3 1/2-inch squares.
Take egg mixture and pour it over the tray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple-crescent dessert
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and place in bottom of greased (sprayed) 9 x 12 pyrex baking dish (or aluminum pan). Bake 8-10 minutes at 350° until done. Cool crust. Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and cool whip together and spread evenly over cooled crust. Sprinkle nuts on top then drizzle with caramel sauce. Refrigerate for 2-4 hours; cut into small pieces placing an apple slice on each piece before serving.

title: barbecue hash
directions: Cook beef until well done.
Combine all other ingredients. Cook 20 minutes.
Take cooked beef and shred it apart; add to cooked ingredients.
Simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with bacon.
Cover bottom of greased baking dish with beef.
Lay chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over all.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered. Serves 8.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine other ingredients, except 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and butter.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs and melted butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken, cool and shred.
Cook broccoli and place in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover with chicken.
Combine first 4 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: buttery crunch topped tomatoes
directions: In small bowl stir together 2 tablespoons melted butter, crushed crackers, cheese and parsley.
Set aside.
In 10-inch skillet melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in caraway seed, salt, pepper and onion.
Add tomatoes.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until tomatoes are heated through (2 to 3 minutes).
Sprinkle with cheese mixture.
Cover; let stand 1 minute.
Serve immediately.

title: mom's bohemian cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease tube pan.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well; add milk and flour alternately (flour sifted with baking powder).
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Bake about one hour; when batter does not stick to toothpick, it is done.

title: pot roast
directions: Season
meat
with
salt
and
pepper and insert garlic pieces if desired.
Sprinkle meat with flour and brown slowly on all sides
in a little hot fat.
Put roast in roaster pan, mix about 1 cup tomato sauce and 1 cup water (depending on the size
of roast).
Pour
around roast, add onion, salt, pepper and a
bay leaf.
Roast
at
until
done.
Baste 2 or 3 times.

title: squash fritters
directions: Drain squash after grating.
Mix everything but the eggs.
Add beaten eggs.
Fry in oil.
Nice summer vegetable.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Place cubed chicken on bottom of large casserole dish.
Spread celery soup, mushroom soup and sour cream over chicken.
Pour chicken broth and margarine in bowl. Add dressing and stir and spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: grand hotel hot fudge sauce(not for the diet conscious)
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add chocolate, sugar and milk. Stir 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add vanilla and salt.

title: no-bake orange peanut butter drops
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, bring sugar, orange juice concentrate and butter to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat; stir in peanut butter until blended.
Add oats and raisins; stir to blend.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: "elvia's fantastic fruit bran muffins"
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Mix cereal and milk in another bowl.
Let stand 3 minutes. Stir in egg, applesauce and Parkay Spread.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened (batter will be lumpy).

title: cream cheese tang pie
directions: Bake pie crust 5 minutes on 350°; take out and let cool. Let cream cheese soften, then mix cream cheese, sour cream and condensed milk in a bowl. Add Tang until it gets light orange or very thick. Pour in graham crust and spread Cool Whip on top. Place in refrigerator for about 3 hours or until set.

title: yellow velvet
directions: Use equal parts of cooked, diced summer squash and cooked corn (fresh or frozen).
Cook each separately and combine.
Add butter, salt, pepper and thick cream to taste.

title: fool proof chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy sauce pan, over low heat, melt morsels with Eagle Brand milk.
Remove from heat, stir in remaining ingredients. Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8 inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board, peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water; stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add cranberry sauce, stirring until blended.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in orange, apple and pecans.
Spoon mixture into 6 lightly oiled 2/3 cup molds or custard cups.
Cover and refrigerate molds until firm.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onions; saute until tender.
Stir in flour, blending well.
Add cabbage, mixing well.
Slowly add water, stirring constantly, and bring to a boil.
Stir in tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar, lemon juice and caraway seed.
Simmer on low heat for at least one hour.
Serves 12.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually, beating well. Add oil, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour batter into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef, then add onion.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; turn to simmer and cover.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peg's layered salad
directions: In a bowl, layer first 8 ingredients in order given (lettuce on bottom, etc.).
Chill for 24 hours.
When ready to serve, salt to taste, toss and top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.
Must be made a day ahead.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix together real good.
Pour into graham cracker crusts. Keep in icebox.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into a ball.
Roll cheese ball into chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: fettuccine with ham
directions: Cook fettuccine as directed on package; drain.
Cook mushrooms in butter, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are light brown. Stir in half and half and cheese; heat just until hot.
Stir in ham that has been chopped coarsely; toss with fettuccine.
Serve with additional grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken on all sides in olive oil over medium heat.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
In same skillet, saute onion for about 1 minute, then add garlic and saute quickly. Add all other ingredients, except mushrooms.
Return chicken to skillet and reduce heat to low.
Cover loosely and simmer for about 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is tender.
Add mushrooms for last 15 minutes of cooking time.
Serve with pasta.
Serves 6.

title: butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Carefully add food coloring as desired.
Beat on high until fluffy.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: First Layer:
Mix and press margarine, flour and pecans in bottom of a pan.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until golden brown, at 350°.

title: switchel
directions: Mix sugar and ginger thoroughly; add vinegar and water.
Shake well and refrigerate.
This is a very good thirst quencher and was often drunk by farmers during haying season.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add molasses and blend.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.
Roll out to 1/4 to 1/8-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut with floured cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.
Decorate.

title: polynesian cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix ingredients by hand. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: penne with sun-dried tomatoes and chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put sun-dried tomatoes in a bowl.
Add boiling water and let soak until you're ready to use.

title: no cook ice cream
directions: Mix the eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla with a mixer.
Pour into your electric ice cream maker can.
Add condensed milk and fruit and stir well.
Add dairy milk and stir, then you can plug it in and let it go.

title: delicious bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator to marinate.

title: eatem right now pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt and celery seed over cucumbers, peppers and onion.
Mix well.
Mix separately the sugar and vinegar.
Mix these cold. Stir real good.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Put into jars and cover. They will keep in the refrigerator up to a month.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a wooden spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in a 9-inch microwave dish or pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped parsley, chives or sage.
Microwave at High power for 10 minutes, rearranging the potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes at High power until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Combine egg, milk, oatmeal and oil in a separate bowl. Add to flour mixture.
Stir only enough to moisten completely. Pour into greased muffin tins, filling them 2/3 full.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lo-cal fruit salad dessert
directions: Drain fruits; combine with apples.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve juice.
Sprinkle Jell-O evenly over fruit, then sprinkle dry cake mix over Jell-O.
Drizzle melted margarine and juice evenly over cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: double chocolate crumble bars
directions: In a large mixer bowl, cream sugar and butter or margarine together thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, chopped nuts, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Spread in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cookies test done.
Sprinkle the marshmallows evenly atop; bake 3 minutes more.
Cool.

title: imperial palace salad
directions: Make a dressing of 4 Tbsp. oil, 2 Tbsp. vinegar and 1/2 tsp. each of salt & tarragon, and a dash of pepper.
Pour over above ingredients.
Chill for hour or longer before serving.
Makes 2 servings.
Delicious.

title: cream cheese and pineapple mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add measured liquid and lemon juice.
Gradually add 2 cups of the gelatin to the cream cheese, blending well.
Chill until thickened, fold in pineapple and spoon into mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat 6 whole eggs until fluffy; add 1 cup sugar.
Beat well. Add 2 cups milk and the vanilla.
Chip 1/4 stick butter; mix thoroughly.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes, then turn back to 325°. Bake about 20 to 25 minutes or until firm.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour and sesaoning.
Add milk all at once.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Add cheese, stir until cheese melts.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Slowly add cheese mixture, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Gradually pour over beaten egg whites, folding in thoroughly.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart souffle dish.
Attach a collar to the souffle dish for a high souffle; measure enough foil (or waxed paper) to go around casserole, plus a 2 to 3 inch overlap.
Fold in thirds lengthwise. Lightly butter one side, letting collar extend 2 inches above the top of casserole.
Fasten with pins around dish (buttered side in).
Bake in slow oven (300°) about 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Gently peel off and serve immediately.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream sugar
and
shortening;
add
eggs and beat well. Add salt
and
baking
powder
to sifted flour.
Add flour and sweet milk alternately; add vanilla.
Pour batter in a greased pan.
Put cherries
over
batter
and bake at 350° until cake tester comes out clean, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar and butter in skillet.
Set over medium heat and boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla; beat until blended evenly.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan and spread to corners.
Chill before cutting into squares.

title: party pizza
directions: Cook meats; drain.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on sliced bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen on cookie sheet before baking and stored in freezer.

title: mac-reuben hot dish
directions: Prepare noodles; drain.
Combine cooked macaroni, ham, pimiento and green onions.
In medium saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese, mustard and pepper. Combine cheese sauce with macaroni mixture.
Put half in 3-quart baking dish; layer with sauerkraut and top with remaining macaroni.
Garnish with diced rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday peas and rice
directions: Saute onion and rice in butter until tender; add garlic powder and broth.
Simmer until done, then add English peas.

title: bee sting cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Mix together brown sugar, milk, butter and nuts; cook until mixture boils; continue boiling for 1 minute.
Pour into 2 cake pans.
Spoon cake mix over syrup mixture so as not to push nuts to side.
Bake to directions on box.
After cake has cooled, frost with following mixture:
Dream Whip prepared as directed on box; add pudding and rum and whip.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: roasted carrots with garlic(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange carrots in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add oil, water and garlic cloves.
Cover with foil and bake until carrots are tender, about 30 minutes.
Uncover and turn carrots.
Bake until lightly brown, about 15 minutes longer. Sprinkle lightly with salt and with freshly ground black pepper to taste and serve.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in oven at 325° until brown.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Grease 3 round cake pans.
Mix cake mix, eggs, mandarin oranges with juice and oil.
Mix until oranges are little slivers. Don't overbeat.
Pour into pans and bake for 20 to 22 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
When cakes are cool, mix Cool Whip, pudding and pineapple.
Mix until Cool Whip is soft.
Put frosting on each layer, top and sides.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Slice chicken.
Place in butter.
Cover with raw rice; pour soup over top and cover with onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased and floured pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and cooled mixture.
Mix well and pour into 2 nine-inch floured cake pans. Top with Carnation icing, Seven Minute or your choice.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stirring well. Dredge potatoes in flour mixture. Layer sliced potatoes in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: sweet-sour turkey
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 1 cup juice.
