Combine juice, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and salt.
Cook over low heat until thickened and clear stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add turkey.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Place green peppers in enough boiling water to cover; let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Add green peppers, onion and pineapple to turkey mixture; heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Put together zucchini, flour, eggs, salt, pepper, oregano, garlic, water and cheese.
Mix well.
Heat the oil.
When hot, drop batter by tablespoons into the oil and fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels!

title: country fair chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken in egg and milk mixture, then in cheese mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Do not have pieces touching.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken and spinach
directions: Squeeze excess liquid out of spinach.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put chicken on top.
Mix mayo, soup, lemon juice and curry. Spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour and syrup, then add all spices, soda and last, adding 1 cup of boiling water.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bread begins to leave sides of pan.
This is soupy, but it is delicious.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Wash lettuce and dry thoroughly.
Break into pieces and toss with thinly sliced onion.
Add sliced berries on top.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over berries about 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken with pieces of celery and onion.
Cook broccoli. Make a basic white sauce using milk and chicken broth.
Cool and add mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and sherry.
Starting with white sauce, layer in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp deviled egg aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Simmer together for 15 minutes the tomato juice, salt, sugar, garlic salt and dried onion soup.
Cool.
Stir gelatin into combined mixture.
Add 1 small can washed small shrimp.
Press 10 deviled egg halves into bottom of ring mold, yolk side down.
Pour chilled tomato-shrimp aspic over eggs.
Allow to set.
Unmold on lettuce leaf.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with fingers until it is crumbly. Set aside.

title: okra patties
directions: Mix okra and egg with a spoon.
Stir in meal.
Spoon drop mixture into a skillet of hot oil, making small patties.
Let brown real good on one side before turning.
You should have to turn only once.
Place patties on a paper towel to remove excess oil.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour
into
greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 325° to 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: deb's blueberry muffins
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, sour cream, soda, baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Add blueberries.
Pour into muffin tins and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: green beans and onion salad
directions: Cook green beans until done, but still firm.
Drain.
Add onions, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, oil and vinegar.
Toss and serve.

title: pumpkin pie ice cream
directions: Stir together and refreeze.
Can put into graham cracker pie crust.
Freeze.
Keep covered.

title: butternut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix sour cream to cooked noodles and add to cooked chicken, broccoli and mushrooms.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is lightly browned.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and oleo.
Cook 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: 7-layer southwestern dip
directions: Line in a 12-inch platter with the lettuce.
Stir together the beans, sweet peppers and onions; spoon atop lettuce, leaving a lettuce border.
Dollop with sour cream; spread gently over bean mixture into a smooth layer.
Sprinkle with jalapenos and 1/3 cup of lime peel, if desired.
Drain excess liquid from salsa and stir in avocado.
Spoon atop of sour cream layer.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with a layer of chopped olives.
Serve with chips.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; then mix in other ingredients.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 350° about 40 to 45 minutes.
Will make two pies.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain, add salt, onion and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add spaghetti, soup, water and mushrooms and garlic powder.
Pour into a 3 qt. casserole dish and top with cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat. Boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn. Put mixture in two shallow pans. Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti the usual way; drain.
Pour into a 1 1/2 or 2-quart greased casserole.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese for topping.
Mix well.
(May be prepared
a day ahead and refrigerated overnight.)
Cheese can be mixed with bread crumbs for topping. Set oven at 350° and bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes or heat in microwave.
Serves 4.

title: stadium spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with vegetables; carrot sticks, celery sticks, broccoli, cauliflower, etc.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter with sugar until fluffy; beat in egg.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Blend well to make stiff dough.
Wrap in wax paper. Chill overnight.
Take 1/2 at a time to roll out on floured board to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out and bake at 350° until light brown, 10 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies well.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add cream cheese. Stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put half cookies in bottom of oblong dish.
Pour mixture over cookies.
Add rest of cookies to top.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with whole cinnamon graham crackers.

title: scallops in shells
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and dot with butter.
These are gourmet in individual shells or can be baked in buttered dish at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a long casserole. Cover with crushed potato chips or Pepperidge Farm crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: quick pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients plus 1/4 cup flour if needed.
Set dough on floured board for 20 minutes.
Cover with bowl.
Oil 2 cookie sheets.
Spread dough on cookie sheets with hands.
Cover dough with tomato sauce or pizza sauce.
Add any or all of the following:
Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, mushrooms, anchovies, sliced black olives, onions and grated Romano cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: make ahead whipped potatoes
directions: Whip the potatoes.
Add sour cream and onion salt. Whip until smooth.
Place in greased casserole. Dot with oleo and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Dip canned biscuits in melted butter then roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Put Oreos in blender or processor, crush and set aside.
In large bowl, mix 10x sugar and cream cheese.
Now add remaining ingredients to bowl except Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in flower pot, cookie base, mix, etc.
Be sure to end with cookies on top.
For decoration, put in artificial flowers with stem wrapped in Saran Wrap.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add cream of mushroom soup and stir until smooth. Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are done.
Serve over rice.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk, add sugar and salt and let cool.
Add yeast to warm water and dissolve.
Add this to milk mixture and add 1/2 of the flour and beat until smooth.
Add egg, shortening and remaining flour.
Knead on floured board.
Bake in cupcake pan.
Pinch off pieces to fill 1/2 of cups, let rise until full.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add cranberry sauce and orange rind. Chill until thickened. Fold in apples, celery and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 9 inch pan and chill until firm.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Put over low heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, to soft ball (236°).
Cool to lukewarm.

title: ina bennett's coffee punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.
Serves 15 to 20.
Whipped cream may be added on top.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cook first 4 ingredients until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add 1 stick oleo, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup pecans.
Beat until smooth and pour in buttermilk dish.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Beat eggs and add one at a time.
Add flour and baking powder.
Alternate with milk.
Add pineapple.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan before removing.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Put into prepared crust.
Bake for 8 minutes; cool.
Chill thoroughly. Top with whipped topping and garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: beef and rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown meat and drain off fat.
Stir in 4 cups of water, 1 teaspoon of salt and remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni-tuna salad
directions: Prepare 1 package of macaroni and cheese.
Then add listed ingredients.
Mix all and chill well.

title: old fashioned tea cakes (mother's recipe) *
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour gradually.
Add baking powder in last cup of flour.
Work like pie crust.
Roll out to desired thickness and cut.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields approximately 50 cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
In saucepan heat cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup and 2 tablespoons butter together.
In casserole place chicken in bottom of dish.
Put soup mixture on top, then put croutons on top with a little broth on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: secret pumpkin soup
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter for 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and pumpkin. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add light cream, honey, nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat through and serve.
Serve in small, hollowed out pumpkins for an added touch.
Sprinkle top with a little nutmeg and top with a small sprig of parsley or fresh chives.

title: marinade for pork
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a marinating container.
Add pork and refrigerate.
Marinate at least 3 hours.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roast sesame seeds, sunflower seeds and almonds approximately 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and add seed mixture.
Toss with your favorite Italian dressing.
Serves 6.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain. Stir in seasoning and pour into casserole lined with chips.
Pour in tomatoes and meat mixture; top with cheese.
Heat at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chili(lean)
directions: Brown turkey, onion and green pepper until meat is no longer pink.
Drain meat, onion and pepper.
Combine all ingredients and simmer.

title: onion meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix ground beef, onion soup mix, milk and egg.
Press firmly in ungreased loaf pan 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 inches.
Loosen edges with a spatula.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add well beaten egg yolks.
To this, add alternately the flour mixture and the milk.
Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Add floured blueberries.
Use a 9 x 9-inch pan or a tube pan, either should be greased and floured.
Sprinkle batter with sugar for a topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Very good.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use about 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice bread into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place bread tightly together in one layer.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Pour half of mixture over bread.
Peel apples, slice and place on bread.
Pour remaining egg mixture over apples.
Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over apples.
Dot with butter. Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Serve with maple syrup.

title: spicy angel cake
directions: In mixing bowl sift together dry flour mixture from cake mix and spices.
Prepare and bake cake according to package directions.
After cool, remove from pan; cut into 1-inch slices. Serve with Maple Fluff Topping.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in boiling salted water until tender. Drain and mash potatoes until smooth (no lumps).
Add remaining ingredients; beat until light and fluffy.
Cool.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
May be used any time within 2 weeks.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook together butter, sugar, salt and sorghum molasses.
Cook to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Mix and pour over popped corn.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook first four ingredients in saucepan until thick.
Cool slightly (15 to 20 minutes).
Peel and chop apples.
Fold into mixture.
Put in 9 x 9-inch dish.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with nuts or cherries.

title: black pepper chicken and mushrooms
directions: Lightly sprinkle chicken with salt, then sprinkle evenly with the pepper, pressing in with your hand.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Saute chicken 3 minutes on each side until lightly browned and cooked through.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon butter to skillet.
Saute mushrooms, tossing for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove and add to chicken.
Add stock to skillet and cook, stirring 1 to 2 minutes, until lightly thickened.
Spoon sauce over chicken and top with mushrooms. Makes 4 servings.

title: scrambled eggs casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and put bread cubes and sausages in bottom of pan.
Beat eggs, milk and salt together and fold in shredded cheese.
Pour mixture over bread and sausages.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: cashew chicken sauce
directions: Dissolve in hot water.
Makes 5 gallons.
Thicken with cornstarch and cold water until real thick.
Serve over breaded chicken chunks, topped with green onion and cashew nuts; serve with rice.

title: caramel pecan rolls
directions: Prepare Pillsbury hot roll mix per package instructions and let rise.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and shredded cheese.
Pour into a greased 10-inch square baking dish. Set aside.
In a blender, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend 30 seconds on high. Pour evenly over broccoli mixture.
Bake on upper rack of oven at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Chop cranberries; mix with 1/4 cup sugar.
Sift together remaining sugar and dry ingredients.
Add nuts and orange rind. Combine egg, milk and melted fat with dry ingredients.
Fold in cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: a happy home recipe
directions: The six most important words in the English language: I admit I made a mistake.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions.
Drain and slice into bite size pieces.
Butter 8-inch square casserole and place cauliflower in bottom.
Drain peas and pour over cauliflower.
Place a few squares of butter on top of peas.
Pour in undiluted soup and spread soup smoothly over top of the ingredients.
Top with grated cheese and then with bread crumbs. Place a few squares of butter on top of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: southern style creamed corn
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart casserole and microwave at High for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in corn, water and sugar.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 3 minutes; stir well and give dish a half turn.
Cover and microwave at High for 5 to 7 minutes or until corn is done.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat with a wire whisk until cornstarch is dissolved.
Add to corn, mixing well.
Cover and microwave at High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring at 1 minute intervals.

title: peanut butter choc. mousse or ice cream
directions: Heat
but
do
not
scald
milk;
stir in cocoa powder. Blend in creamy peanut butter, a small amount at a time until mixture is slightly thickened.
Cool in refrigerator.	Prepare Dream
Whip, beating
to
soft peaks.
Gently blend into cool cocoa-peanut butter mix.
Freeze in small capacity freezer or Donvier ice cream maker.
A portion of the unfrozen mix can be used as a mousse for immediate serving or topping for cake.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook pasta in 1 quart of water with 1 teaspoon of salt. Drain, rinse thoroughly and cool in refrigerator.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Let set in the refrigerator overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, garlic and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, layer half of noodles, meat sauce and cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's famous rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk, sugar and shortening; do not boil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Add enough flour to make soft batter; beat well.
Cover.
Let set for 1 hour (mixture will double in volume).
Add soda, baking powder and salt; beat well.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff.
Knead well to make fine mixture.
(Dough is easier to knead and less sticky if refrigerated for several hours.)
Make as many rolls as desired. Dip in melted shortening, butter or oleo.
Place in greased pan and let rise until double in bulk.
Keep dough in refrigerator and use as needed.
Will keep for 5 days.
If refrigerated, let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Pour juice out of the jar of pickles and rinse them well.
Cut the pickles into chunks and put them back in the jar.
In a saucepan, combine the sugar, vinegar and spices and bring mixture to a boil.
Boil until the sugar is completely dissolved.
COOL completely (very important). Pour the cool liquid over the pickles in the jar and put the lid on.
Turn the jar upside down and put it in your refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, turn the jar right side up and and push the sugar that has gathered at the top down into the juice.
Sweet pickles are now ready to eat.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until blended; add sugar, margarine, flour, milk and vanilla.
Pour into two greased pie pans.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Let set until cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut or pull each biscuit into 4 sections. Mix sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag and shake a few pieces at a time to coat well. Sprinkle nuts in bottom of a well-greased Bundt pan. Drop coated pieces into the pan. Boil brown sugar and margarine for 1 minute. Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn onto a plate and serve warm.

title: country-style chicken soup
directions: In 4 quart or larger crock-pot, combine chicken, onion or leek, carrot, celery, parsley, bay leaf, thyme, salt, pepper and water.
Cover and cook on low 7 or 8 hours or until tender. Remove chicken and bay leaf.
Turn crock-pot on high.
Remove meat from chicken parts; cut into bite-size pieces.
Return chicken to crock-pot; add cooked noodles or rice.
Serve when heated to desired temperature.
Makes 8 or 9 servings.
Each serving contains 188 calories and 6 grams fat.

title: this old house chili beans
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in brown sugar until well mixed. Combine beans, catsup, ground beef, bacon, chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder and hot pepper sauce in a large saucepan. Stir in onion mixture until well mixed.
Cover and simmer over low heat until meat is cooked, about 30 to 35 minutes. Refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
Reheat to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: nutty noodly clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in noodles and nuts so they are evenly coated.
Dip out by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper; chill and refrigerate.

title: asparagus with lemon butter
directions: Combine sliced almonds and 2 tablespoons butter in a pie plate.
Microwave at High for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until almonds are lightly toasted, stirring once.
Drain and set aside.
Combine water and salt in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales from stalks with a knife or vegetable peeler, if desired.
Arrange asparagus in casserole with thick stem ends toward the outside.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High for 6 to 7 minutes, or until crisp-tender, giving dish a half turn after 3 minutes.
Let asparagus stand 3 minutes.

title: grandma brown's cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix together in a quart jar and shake.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.
Perfect for cole slaw or other salads.

title: hot and spicy chicken wings
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Add wings; toss to coat and let stand at least 30 minutes.
Heat broiler.
Arrange wings on broiler pan.
Broil until golden brown. Turn wings over.
Baste with marinade and continue broiling until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Also good dipped in Blue cheese dressing and served with celery sticks.

title: fruit cake
directions: Break mincemeat into small pan; add water.
Heat and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add nuts and all fruit, eggs, milk, flour and soda.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Whip together lightly, sour cream and egg.
Stir egg mixture into dry ingredients; mix lightly.
Turn out on floured board.
Pat out 1/2-inch thick.
Place on lightly buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 425° until lightly browned (about 15 minutes).

title: macaroni salad
directions: In a large saucepan 3/4 full of boiling water, a dash of salt and 1 tablespoon of oil, put macaroni in and cook for about 10 minutes.
Makes sure it's done by trying 1 piece that's cooled a little, then drain in strainer and run cool water over it.
Let drain 5 minutes, shaking occasionally to get more water out.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Mix in celery, cucumber, olives, cheese and mayonnaise.
Add more mayonnaise, if desired.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chuck wagon chili
directions: Cook the beef, onion and seasonings until meat is browned. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
(My kids love this over spaghetti.
We top it with some shredded Cheddar cheese.
Anna brought the recipe home when she was in the first grade and reading about cowboys!)

title: garlic vinaigrette
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar in a small bowl.
Add olive oil in a thin stream, whisking constantly.
Season with pepper and add the garlic clove.
Mix to blend.
For best flavor, let dressing stand for 30 minutes.
Before serving, mix in parsley.
Serves 10 with 95 calories and 10 grams of fat.

title: silver cake (white cake)
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and sift together three times.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add lemon extract.
Fold in egg whites.

title: cornbread dressing(southern style)
directions: Tear meat away from boiled chicken.
Break into small pieces. Beat eggs slightly.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pack lightly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Dressing may be cooked in the bird before roasting. Double the recipe for large birds.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Lightly beat egg in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: chicken in sauce
directions: Mix flour, pepper and salt.
Coat the chicken thighs in this mixture.
Brown in oil in a 14-inch Dutch oven.
Set over 20 coals.
Drain
grease off.	Mix the rest of the ingredients in a separate
pan and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over browned thighs in Dutch oven.
Cook 1 hour with 20 coals on the bottom only.	Turn every 15 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix and put in greased bread pan.
Let rise about 15 minutes. Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken magnifique
directions: Brown cooked chicken in butter.
Stir in soup with mushrooms and 1/8 teaspoon rosemary.
Add chicken and cover and cook.
Serve with rice.

title: crispy onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Soak rings in milk for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Combine milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Dip rings in batter and fry in hot (365°) deep oil until golden.

title: cheesy vegetable bake
directions: Heat Cheez Whiz and margarine until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Add vegetables and put into casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Bake at 350°, about 30 minutes.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: In large cooker, cook beef, celery, carrots and cabbage over medium heat until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and celery in margarine; set aside. Mix together the other ingredients.
Crumble in Ritz crackers. Add crabmeat and mix lightly, adding "set aside" vegetables.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagna alfredo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed and drain. In medium bowl, combine chicken and one jar of alfredo sauce.
In a separate bowl, combine Ricotta and drained cooked spinach.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, place one layer noodles.
Pour chicken and sauce mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella over chicken. Top with another layer of noodles.	Spread spinach mixture over noodles.
Pour 1/2 of remaining jar of alfredo sauce over spinach mixture.
Sprinkle another cup of Mozzarella over sauce.
Layer final noodles layer and top with remaining 2 cups of Mozzarella. Bake 50 to 60 minutes until top is brown and bubbly.

title: pea soup
directions: Simmer ham bone for 1/2 hour.
Add carrots for 15 minutes. Add split peas and onions.
Add salt, pepper and celery (or celery salt) to taste.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: ceviche (shrimp cocktail)equador
directions: Put the shells in a small amount of water and boil for 1 minute. Discard the shells and put shrimp into the water.

Cook until done, set aside reserving the liquid. In a small pan, boil sliced onion (to tame the taste a little) for 1 minute and drain. Mix together the onion, tomato and green pepper, add lime juice, parsley, pepper and salt. Then add shrimp and reserved liquid. Add olive oil and stir.

title: zucchini mexicalli
directions: Brown ground beef, peppers and onions.
When done, add zucchini, chili beans and tomatoes.
Cook for 20 minutes, then add salsa and simmer for another 20 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry-pineapple chiffon pies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberry Jell-O.
Place mixture in refrigerator to cool.
Pour milk into bowl and beat until stiff. Fold into the cooked mixture.
Pour into two 9-inch pie crusts and place in refrigerator until set (about 30 minutes).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Toss together all ingredients except corn flakes and butter. Turn into 12 or 13-inch buttered shallow baking dish.
Top with mixture of corn flakes and butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 12 people.

title: mcdonald kids famous spiced tea mix
directions: Mix 2 teaspoons mix with 1 cup hot water.

title: recipe for a kiss
directions: In a car, use 1/3 of back seat, filter in 1 cup of moonlight. Then add 3 teaspoons of foolishness; set aside with 5 minutes of silences, followed by 3 or 4 romantic glances.
Press calmly on his hand, hesitate, then place lips on his increasing in force.
Draw away, blush lightly, flavor with a gentle squeeze.
Then, set aside to cool.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread in baking dish.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan; set aside.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk; cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly to full rolling boil, then boil without stirring to 234° soft ball stage.
When a drop in cold water forms a ball, remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; don't stir.
Cool to room temperature, then beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens, then quickly spread in pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes about 3 dozen candies.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl and beat until frothy.
Pour into punch bowl.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in greased casserole dish.
Add chicken.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Add condensed mushroom soup and water.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans for a barbecue
directions: In a skillet brown 1/4 cup chopped onions in 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir in a can of Campbell's baked beans, pineapple chunks and prepared mustard.
Heat well.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Pour filling on top of crust; cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken fettucini(serves 4)
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a pan.
Add chicken and cook until chicken is white.
Add wine.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Drain water
from boiled potato.
Mash potato in sugar. (If you
use different flavors, pinch off bits.) Roll dough in long fingers.
Cut
in
1-inch pieces and dip in melted chocolate. Place on waxed paper.
Pecans are optional.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix eggs and soup together. Add broccoli.
Layer soup mixture, 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese and 3/4 cup Pepperidge Farm herb dressing in casserole dish.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, milk and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with glass dipped in margarine, then dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake
minutes
in
350° oven with lid on casserole. Stir and bake 30 minutes more with lid off.

title: sweet bbq ribs
directions: Mix all above ingredients (except ribs) in saucepan and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1/2 to 1-hour stirring occasionally.
Trim ribs as necessary and bake covered at 300 for 45 minutes.
Drain liquid then add BBQ sauce and bake uncovered for another 45 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
In saucepan, heat cheese, oleo and soup until cheese melts.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Peel and finely chop potatoes.
Mix potatoes with onion and sauce.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix corn flakes and oleo and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Place butterscotch chips and peanut butter in top of double boiler; stir occasionally until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and potatoes until both are coated with butterscotch mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Will take 20 to 30 minutes to set.

title: stuffed crab shells
directions: Cook shells as directed on package.
Cool; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together; fill shells and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: low carb meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for 1/4 cup of the spaghetti sauce.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Spread remaining spaghetti sauce over top and let bake an additional 45 minutes.
Makes four hearty servings (8.5 g. carbohydrates per serving).

title: deep dish sugar-free apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Arrange 1 layer of apples in bottom of crust.
Sprinkle with tapioca, Sweet 'N Low and cinnamon.
Arrange second layer of apples and repeat sprinkling as on first layer (same amounts).
Pour in unsweetened apple juice.
Cover with second crust, cutting slits in top to release steam.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 375° and bake for an additional 45 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and roll out on lightly floured board. Cut in round shapes.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: baked potato shells
directions: Bring water to boil in large saucepan.
Add butter, salt and milk.
Remove from heat.
Add instant mashed potatoes, sour cream, cream cheese, garlic powder and chives.
Mix well.
Fill aluminum foil potato shells.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top or if preferred, paprika.
Place shells on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° (the shells freeze very well).
Bakes 14 shells.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and milk; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Preheat oven to 450° and bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Add all ingredients to softened cream cheese, mixing well. Chill and serve with crackers or Triscuits.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper until well blended.
Add milk gradually. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened (about 1 minute).
Add cheese; stir until melted.
In medium pan, dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Add broccoli.
Cook until tender.
(Do not drain liquid.)
Add to cheese mixture and stir until well blended.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 5 to 10 servings.

title: perfect dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 1/4 cup water.
Let stand for 3 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients and put in a greased bowl and cover.
Do not refrigerate.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat all but strawberries 3 minutes.
Add strawberries and bake in 3 layer pans for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent roll dough flat on a cookie sheet, pinching dough together at seams to make 1 flat sheet.
Bake as directed on package until light brown.
Remove and cool.

title: virginia's texas caviar
directions: Mix together.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with tortilla chips. Keeps 2 plus weeks.

title: banana split salad
directions: Crust:
Mix together 1/2 cup melted butter and graham crackers and spread in oblong cake dish.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat the whipping cream until stiff and refrigerate.
Beat the milk, pudding and water for 3 to 4 minutes and refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Fold the pudding mix into the whipped cream.
Spoon over vanilla wafers and bananas arranged in a serving dish.

title: laura ingalls wilder's gingerbread
directions: Blend brown sugar with lard or shortening and molasses and baking soda blended in boiling water.
(Be sure cup is full of water after foam is run off into cake mixture.)

title: seven can soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and warm.
Easy and great!

title: strawberry cream punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sugar, lemonade concentrate and water in punch bowl; mix well.
Stir in ginger ale.
Spoon in ice cream. Serve immediately.
Yields 40 (4 ounce) servings.

title: spiced apple simmer
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven or large pan, combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices; discard.
Serve hot.
Yields 30 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Mix in 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks. Stir in milk. Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Spread small amount on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; cover with layer of vanilla wafers. Top with layer of bananas. Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make 3 layers of each, ending with custard. Beat remaining 3 egg whites stiff, but not dry; gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until mixture forms stiff peaks. Pile on top of pudding, covering entire surface. Bake in preheated hot oven (425°) for 5 minutes or until delicately browned. Serve warm or chilled. Makes servings for 8.

title: spiced rice with almonds
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook and stir almonds in hot oil until light brown; remove and drain on paper towels.
Add onion and garlic to saucepan.
Cook and stir until onion is tender, but not brown.
Stir in uncooked rice, cardamom, ginger, red pepper, cinnamon, cumin and nutmeg.
Cook and stir about 3 minutes to brown the rice.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes; do not lift cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in almonds before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 side-dish servings.

title: lazy daisy frosting
directions: Heat butter and milk until butter melts.
Stir in brown sugar, coconut and nuts.
Spread evenly over hot baked cake in pan. Place low under broiler until lightly brown and bubbly.
Frost top of one 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: aunt maxine's peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and butter; mix well.
Whip the cream; add vanilla and fold into the peanut butter mixture.
Put in chocolate pie crust; dribble chocolate syrup over and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: spicy fast fiesta soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine tomatoes, corn and beans. Heat through. Garnish servings with cheese and sour cream, if desired. Serves 4.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Shape in small balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Take the bottom of small glass, press in sugar, then press on top of each cookie and press down.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco skillet
directions: In 12-inch skillet, over high heat, cook beef, onion and garlic until well browned.
Pour off fat.
Stir in tomato puree and remaining ingredients except tortilla chips and cheese.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: baked apple dish
directions: Place apple filling or topping in a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples. Bake at 375° for almost 30 minutes, or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fat bread
directions: Melt butter and shortening.
Add eggs, milk and flavorings. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix and bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours (sometimes longer).
Test with a knife.
This makes a very rich dessert bread.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt half cup of butter with brown sugar; mix well to make sauce.
Set aside.
Melt remaining half cup butter, cut biscuits into fourths, one package at a time.
Mix cinnamon and white sugar.
Dip biscuits pieces into melted butter and then roll in the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Layer first package of biscuits in the bottom of a well-greased Bundt pan. Top with 1/3 of brown sugar sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of pudding powder.
Repeat for remaining two layers.
Raisins or nuts may be added to the layers, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Turn out on serving platter and pull apart to serve.

title: creamy chocolate frozen yogurt
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in milk and Egg Beater. Cook and stir over low heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate syrup and cool.
Stir in vanilla and yogurt.
Freeze in ice cream maker.
Yields 1 quart.
Contains 0 g. fat, 0 mg. cholesterol and 152 calories.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well. Add flour; blend well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: turkey spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute pepper, onion and garlic in olive oil.
Mix in salsa, basil, cilantro and beef broth.
Add Ragu and simmer 1 hour. Serve over pasta.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
If desired, serve with whipped cream.
(Makes 8 servings.)

title: buckeyes
directions: Soften butter and knead ingredients together.
Roll into tiny balls and refrigerate to set.
Melt two packages chocolate chips and 1/2 stick paraffin wax in double boiler.
Use toothpicks to dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Put on wax paper or greased cookie sheet.

title: oyster supreme
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Layer the two mixtures starting with the cracker mixture and ending with it.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Butter the pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls to fit onto a jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar together. Stir in bananas and egg. Add vanilla and other ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour, salt and pepper steak.
Brown in oil.
Cut in 2 pieces. Put some flour into drippings.
Brown.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Place steak in shallow pan. Pour liquid and veggies over.
Place in a 350° oven.
Cook for 2 hours or until tender.
Sprinkle cheese just before removing from oven.

title: sourdough bread bowl dip
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Cut off top of bread 1 inch from top and hollow out loaf with a fork to form a bowl.
Reserve with bread pieces in an airtight bag to use as dippers.
Mix the remaining ingredients to make the dip and pour into the hollowed out loaf. Replace top and wrap entire loaf in foil.
Bake for 3 hours. Serves approximately 15.
This is a big hit at parties even with people who don't like clams.
You may want to buy an extra loaf of sourdough bread to cut up into bite size pieces for dipping, also.

title: empress chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add other ingredients in a big saucepan; add hamburger.
Mix well.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese and onions on cooked spaghetti.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and bake in a preheated oven for 7 minutes the pretzels, sugar and margarine.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into 4 sections and boil until soft.
Test with a fork.
In a large pot, slightly melt butter with parsley. Drain potatoes and mix with butter and parsley.
Toss or stir gently.
Serve hot.

title: pina colada pies
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese in bowl until smooth.
Beat in half the whipped topping.
Spread in pie shells. Chill in refrigerator.
Combine pudding mix and milk in bowl, mixing well.
Fold in pineapple.
Spoon over chilled cream layers. Top with remaining whipped topping.
Garnish with nuts and coconut.

title: spinach salad
directions: Place cut up spinach in bowl.
Add crumbled bacon and green onions and toss.
Add vinegar, water, dressing mix and sugar to bacon fat in skillet.
Heat to boiling and pour over spinach. Toss and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: spider cake
directions: You will need 8 (12-inch) black bump chenille pipe cleaners, 1/2 pair vampire teeth and 2 plastic cat eyes.

title: hamburger squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion and drain.
Mix all ingredients into a casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broiled chicken
directions: Rub chicken pieces, halves or quarters with soft butter or margarine.
Place, skin side down, on broiler rack.
Place broiler rack and pan in broiler so that surface of chicken is 6 to 8 inches from the source of heat.
Broil for 20 to 30 minutes.
Season, turn; brush with margarine.
Broil 15 to 20 minutes longer or until brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour
cup
sugar
over sliced peaches.
Let stand. Make batter
of flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and milk. Melt butter
in
baking pan.
Pour in batter, then peach mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made with other fruit.

title: corn bread skillet meal
directions: Heat oil in skillet on medium heat.
Add onions and ground beef and brown.
Drain off fat.
Add seasonings, soup and water; bring to a boil.
Beat egg slightly.
Add milk.
Mix with corn muffin mix.
Pour evenly over meat mixture in skillet.
Cover and cook on low or simmer heat for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: plain cake
directions: Sift flour baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Combine two mixtures and stir until smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 365° for 25 minutes.

title: bacon stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop stems, onion and green pepper.
Chop bacon.
In saute pan, cook bacon until almost done. Add onion and green pepper.
Saute 2 to 4 minutes.
In mixing bowl, combine mixture with cream cheese.
Stuff mushroom caps with cream cheese mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening; add milk.
Turn on lightly floured board.
Roll 1/4-inch thick in a rectangle.
Cut into 6 equal squares.
Cover each square with peeled and thinly sliced apples.
Top each with generous amounts of white and brown sugar and 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and dash of salt.
Wrap dough around apples and form a ball.
Place in casserole.
Slice apples over dough balls.
Top with some sugar, cinnamon, etc.
Pour 1/2 full with hot water.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes, until apples are done.

title: six-layer sausage casserole
directions: Lightly brown sausage; drain on paper towel and cut into small pieces.
Into a 2-quart dish, place the vegetables in order given. Sprinkle with seasoning mixed together and top with sausage. Cover and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple butter
directions: Prepare jars for processing.
Cut apples into quarters (do not peel).
In heavy 7-quart saucepan over high heat, bring apples and cider to boil.
Reduce heat; cook 15 minutes until apples are tender.
Into a very large bowl, press apple mix through food mill.
Return apple pulp to pan; add sugar, cinnamon and cloves. Cook about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until thick, dark and mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Remove from heat.
Ladle mixture into jars, leaving about 1/4-inch space at top.
Makes 10 (8 ounce) jars.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into pieces.
Add sliced onions, broken into rings and chopped green peppers to broccoli and cauliflower. Then mix together Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar and pour over the vegetables.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: sweet salad dressing
directions: Cook until thick and cool; when cold, beat in 1 cup whipped cream.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Stir in the other ingredients.

title: turkey wild rice soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine broth and water.
Add rice and onion; simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until rice is tender.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In medium saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Add half and half; cook 2 minutes until mixture thickens slightly, stirring constantly.
Slowly add half and half mixture to rice mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly.
Garnish with bacon or parsley.
Makes 8 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: microwave french onion soup
directions: Heat butter and onions in 3-quart covered microwave casserole for 7 minutes.
Stir in broth, water, wine, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Stir.
Cook for additional 12 minutes.
Top with croutons and cheese.
Makes about 4 large servings.

title: deviled pork chops
directions: Peel potatoes and onions.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Layer in roaster and arrange pork chops on top.
Blend catsup, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar with water.
Pour over chops and bake covered in a moderate oven at 375° for 1 3/4 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Baste during baking.
Remove cover and bake for 30 minutes longer allowing meat to brown.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add tomato sauce, chili powder, vegetables and baking powder biscuit mix.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: taco pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco sauce together and spread on large platter.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, water, cream of tartar and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
In a small bowl, very slowly pour the hot sugar syrup over the unbeaten egg whites, beating constantly until stiff peaks form.
Add vanilla.

title: seafood dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Add your choice of seafood (tiny shrimp or clams; Louis Rich artificial crab is what I used. I remove the red stuff around the edges).
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl combine margarine, peanut butter and sugar; mix well.
Shape in 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt white chocolate in double boiler.
Dip balls and place on waxed paper to harden.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine the oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and dash of salt. Cut in the margarine and mix well. Peel and slice the apples.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with the sugar.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture over all.
Microwave 10 minutes on Medium or bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use a 2-quart Ultra 21 casserole dish.
Serves 6.

title: grandmom's cucumber dip
directions: Grate cucumbers, celery and onion in blender.
Drain well. Mix all together.
Serve with chips.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat
eggs
slightly,
add
milk,
Bisquick, butter and salt. Pour
into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle the cheese and meat on
top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Recipe may be doubled and put in oblong dish.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add remaining liquid to desired moist consistency.
Mold into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: favorite chocolate pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together (flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons cocoa) and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread batter in an ungreased pan (9 x 9-inches).
Mix brown sugar, 4 tablespoons cocoa and hot water.
Pour over mixture and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad with bacon
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with dressing. Serve 8-10.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Add sifted flour and spices.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix soda with hot applesauce and add to dry mixture.
Bake at 300° to 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill at least six hours.

title: phenomenal fudge
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan; add cocoa and sugar.
Mix well.
Then add evaporated milk and syrup.
Cook until boiling, stirring constantly.
Clip candy thermometer to side of pan; reduce heat.
Cook to 230°.
Pour mixture into glass bowl.
Cool until thermometer reads 100°.
Hand beat mixture until it looks like frosting; pour into buttered square 8 x 8-inch pan and spread evenly.
Cut into squares.

title: scotch oatmeal shortbread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and salt.
Add flour.
Blend.
Add almond flavoring.
Add oats.
Press onto cookie sheet to form rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into strips length and breadth of little finger.
Separate cookies.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°. Leave on pan until cool.
Very festive if decorated with frosting rosettes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Put hot water on poppy seed and let stand a few minutes.
Mix cake, eggs, pudding, oil and poppy seed water.
Mix all together. Bake in 2 large greased bread tins for 50 minutes at 350°. Delicious!

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Make meat into bite size meatballs.
Drop into boiling water for 5 minutes.
Take out and put into baking dish.
Mix and melt over low heat, chili sauce and grape jelly.
Pour over meatballs and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: charlotte's old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water 15 minutes.
Drain into cup. Add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tropical cooler
directions: Stir together orange juice, lemonade and apple juice.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Serve over ice.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: angel food pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool and top with whipped cream and chopped pecans.

title: greta's favorite "salsa"(soon to be yours!)
directions: Combine 1 can of the first 3 ingredients and the next 2 ingredients.
Blend lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to desired consistency.
Refrigrate.
Serve with chips.

title: surprise chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Baste chicken 2 or 3 times during baking.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate.
Stir in milk and nuts, stirring until thick. Drop by the spoonful.

title: gnocchi
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes in water until tender.
Drain and peel. Put through ricer or mash until very smooth.
Heap the potatoes on a board; add half the flour and make a well in the center.
Drop in the egg and knead mixture into a smooth firm dough.
Coat board and hands with flour.
Break dough into large pieces and, using the palms of your hands, roll into a 3/8-inch snake.
Cut into 1 1/4-inch pieces and gently roll over the prongs of a fork, pressing lightly with your thumb to make the characteristic ridges.
They will curl a little.
When complete, drop a few at a time in boiling, salted water.
When they rise to the surface (about 3 minutes), they are done.
Lift out with slotted spoon and place on a heated platter.
When all are cooked, top with your favorite good spaghetti sauce and grated cheese.

title: deep dish peach pie
directions: Place peaches in 8 inch square baking dish.
Mix flour sugar and cinnamon well.
Stir into peaches.
Dot top with small pieces of butter.
Roll out biscuit dough on floured surface and cut into lattice strips and place over peaches.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon sugar if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: veggie salad
directions: Microwave oil, sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved. Pour over veggies.
Chill overnight to several days.
Season with salt and pepper before serving.
Makes 24 servings.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green pepper, 1/2 cup picante sauce and cream cheese in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture onto each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in lightly greased baking dish.
Stir cheese and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Pour sauce over tortillas. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated. Pour remaining picante sauce over tortillas.

title: paul's spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine
first eight ingredients; mix well.
Shape into meatballs and brown in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese.
Boil and reduce heat to simmer for 4 to 6 hours covered.
Stir occasionally.	Serves 4 to 6 (double or triple ingredients, if necessary).

title: "snickerdoodles"
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: skillet beef-n-beans
directions: Cut beef in strips.
Brown in oil.
Add onion, beans and celery; cook 4 to 6 minutes.
Stir.
Mix the cornstarch, soy sauce and mushroom liquid.
Add to skillet, along with mushrooms.
Stir, cooking, until liquid is shiny.
Cover and cook until beans are tender.
Garnish with pimiento.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: saints a la mode
directions: Even though the saints seem to be extraordinary people, they are made from average persons just like you and me.
Add the faith, hope and charity to the human being, stirring constantly. Mix in the sufferings slowly to prevent spoiling.

title: microwave smoked sausage and peppers
directions: Cook pasta.
Toss with 1/4 cup dressing; add tomato.
Set aside.
Combine olive oil, peppers, asparagus and garlic in a container.
Cover; microwave on High until vegetables are tender, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Place sausage and remaining dressing in another container.
Cover; microwave on High until sausage is hot, about 3 to 6 minutes.
Combine sausage and pepper mixtures; serve over pasta.
Serves 6.

title: feather sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Add water and continue beating until very thick.
Gradually add sugar, then extracts.
Fold in flour sifted with salt, a little at a time. Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar and beat until they form moist, glossy peaks.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Bake in 10-inch ungreased angel-cake pan in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.
Invert pan to cool.

title: green salad
directions: Mix the last four ingredients together with a mixer and pour over the vegetables.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: turkey, chicken or ham buffet casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Melt margarine; stir in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove.
Add cheese.
Arrange noodles, broccoli and meat in shallow casserole.
Pour cheese sauce over.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: punch for 100
directions: Mix all together and serve chilled.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool and cut up in small pieces. Add sour cream and grated Cheddar cheese to chicken and garlic powder to taste.
Fill each flour tortilla shell with 2 tablespoons of filling.
Roll up and place in a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar.
Heat milk until very warm (not hot).
Dissolve yeast in milk.
Pour into flour.
Add beaten eggs, melted butter and cinnamon.
Add flour (enough to be able to handle dough).
Knead dough; put into greased bowl.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Punch down.
Knead again.
Let rise 30 minutes more.
Punch down.
Brush with melted butter.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peach melba
directions: This is a great dessert to serve at a small luncheon or dinner party.
Before guests arrive, place a slice of cake with one peach half on top into individual dessert dishes or long stem glasses. Refrigerate.
At dessert time, heat preserves on low in saucepan until they become loose and soft.
Spoon hot preserves over the cake and peach.
Add one large scoop of ice cream on top and more hot preserves.
Add a scoop of Cool Whip and add a cherry on top.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: pop's lime congealed salad
directions: Drain juice from cocktail.
Bring to almost boiling.
Use this to mix with Jell-O and stir well.
Let cool, but not congeal.
Add other ingredients together.
Mix with Jell-O and let congeal.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine zucchini, sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
(I do this in the blender.)
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to liquid mixture.
Mix well.
Add chopped nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: scones
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar. With a pastry blender, cut in margarine until particles are fine.
Stir in currants and raisins. In small bowl, beat egg and cream until blended. Add to flour mixture and stir with fork until moistened. Form dough into a ball and turn out on floured cloth.
Roll to 8-inch round, 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 4 quarters, then cut each into 3 wedges. Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush tops with egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
With thumb, make an indentation in broad section of each scone. Fill with 1/4 teaspoon jam.
Bake in a 400° oven about 15 minutes.
Serve warm with extra jam or honey.
Makes 12. Indentation may be made with a pointed teaspoon 1/8-inch deep.

title: quaker's best oatmeal cookies
directions: May add 1 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped nuts or 1 cup raisins and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.
Bake at 350°.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine cream of mushroom soup and mayonnaise.
Mix vegetables and add the other mixture.
Combine well and pour into casserole. Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.

title: corn dogs(club member: john waters)
directions: Roll out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Put slice of cheese on roll, then hot dog with stick in it.
Roll up and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tailgate dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread softened cream cheese. Pour Hormel chili over cream cheese.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and dish is heated through, approximately 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Remove outside leaves and wash cabbage.
Shred to measure 5 cups.
In saucepan, heat 1/2-inch salted water and 2 tablespoons vinegar to boiling.
Add cabbage.
Cover and heat to boiling; cook about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Fry bacon; drain.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Stir brown sugar and flour into drippings in skillet.
Add water, 1/4 cup vinegar, salt, pepper and onion. Cook, stirring frequently, until thick, about 5 minutes.
Add bacon and sauce to cabbage and heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon cheesecake pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make a crust with graham crackers and margarine.
Combine sugar, eggs, vanilla and soft margarine and beat for 15 minutes with mixer.
Spread on crust; add bananas and pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top and decorate with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate!

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Prepare cake mix; pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake as directed.
With electric mixer, beat cheese until fluffy.
Slowly add milk until smooth.
Add dry pudding mix and beat until thickened; refrigerate.
Allow cake to cool in pan. After cooled, spread pineapple on top of cake.
Spread pudding mixture over cake; cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate (covered) well before serving.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook ground beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: pepperoni alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini; keep warm.
Melt butter in large pan.
Stir in half and half, nutmeg and pepper; cook and stir for 5 minutes, or until mixture thickens slightly.
Stir in cheese; cook over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Immediately stir in pepperoni and fettucini.
Toss to coat with sauce.

title: no bake peanut brownies
directions: Combine nuts, graham crackers, powdered sugar and peanut butter in large bowl.
Blend well; set aside.
Heat chocolate and milk in small saucepan over low heat.
Stir constantly until smooth; remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Measure 1/2 cup of the chocolate mix; set aside.
Combine remaining mix with crumb mix. Spread evenly in a well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread measured chocolate mix to glaze.
Chill and cut.

title: banana bran nut bread
directions: Combine egg, bananas, shortening and bran.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Add nut meats and mix well.
Add to banana mixture, mixing only enough to dampen all flour.
Turn into a well-greased bread pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch) and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until bread is done.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Dissolve the jello in water and let cool.
Separate the egg yolks from the whites and beat yolks thoroughly and add the sugar and lemon rind and the juice.
Beat well.
Add dash of salt.
To this mixture, add the whipped cream, beaten egg whites and then the jello last.
Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with graham cracker crumbs.
Put pie mixture in dish and then sprinkle with the remaining graham cracker crumbs and freeze.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Layer the pineapple in cake pan. Put 1 bag of peaches next, then the dry cake mix, then the other bag of peaches, then brown sugar, melted butter and raisins. Bake at 350 degrees for about 1 hour. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: old fashion apple pie
directions: *If using sweet apples, use only 1 cup sugar.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in water. Cook, without stirring, to 225° on the candy thermometer or until hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour gradually over beaten egg whites.
While beating constantly, add vanilla. Continue beating until candy cools and will hold shape.
Next drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper or spread into buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup butter, sugar and eggs.
Whip with mixture. Spread on graham crackers.
Slice a layer of bananas and pineapple over mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Mix with chicken and mushroom soup, cheese, broccoli and 1 cup rice. Grease a large casserole dish.
Line with 2 cups of rice.
Add broccoli mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Heat in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken, farmer style(pollo contadino, italian)
directions: Season the chicken lightly with salt and pepper.
Place the chicken in a large bowl and add the flour.
Toss together and pat off excess flour.
Heat a large frying pan and add half the olive oil.
Brown the chicken on both sides and remove to a roasting pan, leaving the oil in the frying pan.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients, except nuts and chips.
Mix well.
Add nuts and chips.
Pour into Bundt pan. Place on lowest rack of oven at 350°.
Bake for 60 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Into a bowl, put 2 cups warm water, sugar, salt, shortening and dissolved yeast.
Add 3 cups flour and beat well.
Gradually add remaining flour to form a smooth soft dough.
Knead dough on a lightly floured board about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise to double in bulk.
Punch down.
Turn out on board and divide in half (for smaller loaves, divide into the number of loaves you plan to bake) and let rest 15 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Cover with damp towel and let rise to double in bulk.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies(calorie-trimmed)
directions: Mix flour, granulated sugar, soda, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add brown sugar, butter, egg, yogurt and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in oats; chill.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for about 8 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use deep 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Mix soup and soy sauce until smooth.
Add green beans, 1/2 of onions, and pepper.
Mix well.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining onions over beans and bake 5 minutes longer or until onions are crisp.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough into bottom of a 12-inch pizza pan.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes at 350° or until slightly browned.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together until smooth. Spread over cooled crust.
Top with assorted fruits.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Place halved chicken breasts on broccoli.
Combine soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: barbecue sloppy joes
directions: In frypan, cook hamburger and drain.
Add sauce and water, covering hamburger.
Add chilies; cook until warm to hot.
Pour over buns.

title: low-fat egg and cheese bake
directions: Grease 11 x 14 inch pan. Remove crust from bread and tear into pieces. Place bread in pan. Blend Egg Beaters and skim milk until frothy. Add mustard and seasoning. Add shredded cheese and pour over bread. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine flour and 1 cup walnuts; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or a round loaf of rye or pumpernickel bread.
Hollow out the loaf and use as bowl.
Use center to make cubes for dipping.

title: chile salsa(hot tomato-pepper sauce)
directions: Caution:
Wear
rubber gloves while handling chilies or wash hands thoroughly with soap and water before touching your face. Peel and prepare chile peppers as follows: Wash and dry chilies. Slit
pepper
on
its side to allow steam to escape. Peel peppers using one of the following methods.

title: no-bake lasagna
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, slice mushrooms, dice tomato and chop onion.
With vegetable peeler, shave strips of Parmesan cheese for topping.

title: easy pig-in-blankets
directions: Roll crescent rolls out.
Spread mustard on crescent rolls. Roll hot dogs with a piece of cheese in crescent rolls.
Bake in oven until brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put the popped corn and peanuts in a large roaster. Set aside. Mix the oleo, brown sugar and corn syrup on medium-high heat. Stir often. Bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add 1 teaspoon soda and mix well. Pour over corn and nuts; mix well. Put in a 250° oven for 45 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes. Dump on wax paper.
When cool, break apart.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package,
less one cup milk.
Blend pudding mix with cool whip.
Layer crackers and pudding mixture.
You may not need all of the crackers, it's according to the container you use.
Finish with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate for about an hour before serving.

title: cheesy chicken tortilla stack
directions: Combine sour cream, salt and hot sauce.
Place 1 tortilla on lightly greased baking sheet; spread about 1 tablespoon sour cream mixture over tortilla.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chicken, 1/4 cup Monterey Jack, 1/4 cup Longhorn and 2 tablespoons onions.
Repeat layers 4 times.
Top with remaining tortilla.
Reserve remaining sour cream mix.
Brush top and sides of tortillas with margarine. Cover with foil; bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Immediately remove foil after baking.
Place tortilla stack on serving plate.
Spread remaining sour cream mixture on top; sprinkle with lettuce and tomato.
Cut into wedges and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Work in all ingredients thoroughly by hand.
Roll in 2 large balls and then roll in paprika.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine sugars, buttermilk, soda, salt and margarine in 2-quart glass mixing bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 7 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in pecans.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 11 to 12 minutes or until candy reaches soft ball stage, stirring every 4 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: zucchini pizzas
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; still well.
Spoon 1 1/2 teaspoon cheese mix on each zucchini slice.
Top each with a slice of mushroom and a slice of olive.
Broil 6 inches from heat 3 to 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve immediately.
Yields:
2 dozen appetizers (19 calories each). 1.1 g protein, 1.1 g fat, 1.5 g carbohydrate, 2 mg cholesterol, 29 mg sodium and 26 mg calcium.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and vinegar together.
Boil to hard boil stage.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into popped corn and stir very fast.
When cool enough to work with, grease hands and form balls.

title: herbed fried parsnips
directions: Pare parsnips, cut lengthwise into 1/8 inch slices. Cook, covered in small amount of boiling salted water for 12 minutes or until tender. (Lift lid 3 or 4 times during cooking time.) Remove parsnips slices from water. Dip slices in beaten eggs and then in mixture of bread crumbs, salt and rosemary. Saute in hot shortening until brown on both sides.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Crumble cake in bowl.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar together; make thin and pour on cake.
Mix strawberries and glaze together and pour on top of other mixture.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Put jello and marshmallows in 1 cup boiling water. Stir until marshmallows are dissolved.
Put in refrigerator to chill. Whip the cream.
Mix well the
cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Mix with the jello mixture and put in refrigerator.
Chill until set.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. To serve, put 2 tablespoons in a mug of hot water.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Combine raisins and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add next five ingredients which have been mixed into a smooth paste.
Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add white sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff peaks are formed.
Top pie filling with meringue and bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: carol's famous raspberry bars
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, flour, baking soda and salt with fork.
Add oats.
Spread slightly more than 1/2 of oatmeal mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread jam evenly over oatmeal mixture. Crumble remaining oatmeal mixture over the top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: coconut pie filling
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch and add to heated milk; stir.
Beat egg yolks; add to filling, stirring it well.
Add 1 tablespoon coconut, vanilla and 1 tablespoon butter as it thickens.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Let cool about 10 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat until rice is tender.
Add butter, sugar, vanilla, lemon rind, raisins and eggs.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Add sour cream and vanilla to dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Combine remaining sugar and nuts.
Put half of batter in well-greased tube pan.
Pour in half of sugar-nut mixture.
Add remaining batter and remaining topping.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in a 10-inch tube pan.
Invert on plate when cool.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion; cook for a few minutes.
Drain. Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.
Add a dash of garlic powder, tomato sauce and water.
Cook until well blended.
Put cooked, drained spaghetti into casserole dish.
Pour meat sauce over top of spaghetti.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted and browning around edges.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Shake well to mix.
Chill. Makes 1 cup.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat for 30 seconds on low speed, then medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into two 9-inch greased cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool pans for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool on the wire rack.
Mix together the pudding and the pineapple; stir 2 minutes.
Mix in Cool Whip and then frost the cake; keep refrigerated.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Cook hamburger.
Put beef in 9-inch pie shell.
Mix cheeses, onion, mayonnaise, milk, cornstarch, eggs and pepper.
Pour over beef.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain.
Add chili mix and tomato sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Cut Velveeta into small cubes.
Put 1/2 of the Velveeta on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with meat mixture. Top with remaining Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve with nachos.

title: brownie torte
directions: Grease two 9-inch cake pans.
Prepare brownie mix as directed for cake brownies.
Pour into pans.
Bake 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.
Mix 1/2 cup milk and pudding.
Chill 10 minutes.
Mix Eagle Brand and Cool Whip into pudding.
