Spread 1/2 of mixture on brownie layer.
Spread on 1/2 of fruit.
Place 2nd brownie layer on this.
Top with pudding mixture and rest of fruit.
Store in refrigerator.

title: nacho's delicious
directions: In large skillet or electric skillet cook ground chuck and drain.
Cook onion in skillet with 2 Tbsp. butter, 3 Tbsp. worcestershire sauce, and 3 Tbsp. soy sauce.
Cook until soft. Add onion, mushrooms, tomato sauce, rotel, pasta sauce, salsa, pizza sauce, and 2 cans tomatoes.
Let simmer 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 250°.

title: toffee
directions: Heat sugar and butter in a pan until melted.
Add milk, little by little.
Move
(stir)
until
it
takes
consistency (until it pulls away from
the pan and spoon, hardball stage). Add 5 to 6 drops of lemon juice from fresh lemon.
Pour into a greased pan (until set).

title: bean casserole with sour cream
directions: Simmer onion in melted butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Add sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Cook beans according to package directions and drain well.
Mix with sour cream.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Place 30 x 18-inch heavy-duty aluminum foil in baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Place meat on foil.
Sprinkle soup mix over top of meat and spread with cream of mushroom soup.
Fold foil over meat and seal securely.
Cook in 300° oven for 4 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: simple soy milk
directions: Soak
overnight.
Heat in same water and bring to boil. Lower heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour off foamy liquid and add cold water to stop cooking process.
Whiz 3 cups at a time on liquefy.
Add water
until
milk
consistency. Strain through cheesecloth.
If cooking,
no
need to strain.
For milk, add honey, vanilla and pinch of salt to taste.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: * In cheesecloth bag.

title: cheesy crab rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on bread rounds. Broil until cheese bubbles (3 to 4 minutes).
Yields 24 appetizers.

title: honey garlic spareribs
directions: Season ribs with garlic salt.
Arrange in baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour until tender.
Drain all liquid.
Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan and simmer 5 minutes.
Drizzle honey mixture over ribs and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Baste every 10 minutes.

title: tuna fish in double boiler
directions: Combine in top of double boiler until hot.
Make into sandwiches.
Makes 4 or 5 sandwiches.

title: mom's favorite bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop the green onions and mix together with the cheese and mayonnaise.
Cut the bread in half lengthwise. Spread the mixture on both halves of the bread and place them open face on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until the cheese melts.

title: cinnamon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Serve with fruit slices or cookies.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 cup of dip.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Combine soy sauce, pineapple juice, vegetable oil, sugar, garlic powder, ginger, mustard and pepper and bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over 1-inch cubes of boned chicken breasts in a shallow dish.
Cover and marinate at least 1 hour. Skewer chicken and vegetables and grill, basting with marinade sauce.

title: lasagne al forno(classic corner)
directions: Brown beef in oil in 3-quart saucepan.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook lasagne according to package directions.
Drain.
(Separate lasagne and lay out flat on wax paper or aluminum foil to keep pieces from sticking together as they cool.)
Spread about 1/2 cup meat sauce on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with layer of lasagne.
Add some of the Mozzarella and Ricotta cheeses and cover with sauce. Repeat layers of lasagne, meat sauce and cheeses, ending with a layer of lasagne and sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Remove foil and bake 5 minutes longer. Allow to stand about 10 minutes before cutting for easier handling. Makes 8 servings.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Brown meat slowly in hot oil; remove from heat.
Drain. Sprinkle meat with salt.
Combine vinegar and all remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Return to heat.
Cover tightly. Simmer until tender 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Remove meat to serving platter.
Skim off excess fat from juices.
Spoon over meat.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to instructions.
When cooked, add cheese, margarine and soups.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Add to rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Butter and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder in a large bowl; mix well.
In a separate bowl, blend oil and eggs into strawberries; add to flour mixture.
Stir in nuts, blending until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Divide batter between pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool in pans on rack for 10 minutes.
Turn loaves out; cool completely.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: coconut squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top of pie and cook 15 minutes more.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry-lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add lemon extract and mix well.
Dredge blueberries in 2 teaspoons flour; fold into batter.
Pour into 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes until done.

title: apple bars
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Beat sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add the Crisco oil and vanilla.
Fold in the apples.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate no-bake oatmeal cookie
directions: Put sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil.
Reduce heat to medium boil.
Boil 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, oats and nuts.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: swiss vegetable medley(serves 7)
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 Swiss cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake covered 30 minutes at 350°, then top with remaining cheese and onion rings, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: cookie dessert
directions: Press cookie dough into 12-inch pizza pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding with the milk. Beat in the Cool Whip. In a large bowl, layer vanilla wafers then a layer of sliced bananas. Pour pudding over bananas. Layer wafers and bananas then more pudding. Do this several times ending with the pudding. Crumble 2 or 3 wafers on top.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift
flour
and sugar together.
In small pan, combine butter, cocoa
and	water.	Bring
to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour and
sugar; mix well.
Add milk, cinnamon, vanilla, eggs and soda.
Mix	well.
Pour
into
greased
and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate and Coffee Frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion.
Pour soup and Cheez Whiz into this.
Stir well until all is melted.
Add black pepper and several dashes of hot sauce.

title: microwave quiche
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a microwave dish.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes.

title: shrimp in packet
directions: You will also need 4 (12-inch) squares aluminum foil or greased heavy brown paper.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in covered double boiler until thickened and rice is done (approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours).

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add flour and sugar.
Mix in margarine.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour.
Do not overcook.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream!!!

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add crumbs and sugar.
Press in 8 or 9-inch square pan and chill.
Beat soft cream cheese.
Add condensed milk, lemon and vanilla.
Pour over crumbs and chill at least 4 hours.
Mix together relish, rind and nuts.
Cover mixture.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix pineapple, juice and bread cubes in a bowl; set aside. In another bowl, mix eggs and sugar. Combine both mixtures and put in a Pyrex bowl. Bake 40 minutes at medium heat.

title: fruit salad pie
directions: Make 2 pie shells and, when cool, sprinkle with coconut.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Grate rind of lemon.
Mix with lemon juice, jello, sugar and water.
Let set until partially set. Whip chilled milk.
Add to jello mixture. Roll out.
Put graham crackers on bottom of pan until covered. Spread jello mixture over crumbs. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: tangerine macaroons
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat egg whites and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form. Fold in coconut, pecans and peel.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 1 1/2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Remove and cool.
Makes about 36.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLime brand and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell; bake 8 minutes.
Cool. Chill.
Spread with topping.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Blend the butter into the sugar and cocoa and stir on heat to make warm.
Stir in milk; bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Pour Jell-O packages into bowl and add boiling water.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add the cold water and chill until set.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Cut celery into small pieces.
Set aside.
When Jell-O is set, whip the Jell-O until light and fluffy.
Mix the cream cheese with the Jell-O.
Add and stir in the celery.
Nuts may be added if desired.
Put the mixture into a serving bowl and put it into refrigerator to set until serving time.

title: panocha(zasu pitts' recipe)
directions: This candy is foolproof.
If it hardens too quickly, just add a little more cream and it will come out perfect.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Thinly slice beef into bite-size strips.
Combine flour and sour cream.
Stir in bouillon granules, 1/2 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, cook and stir half of the meat in margarine or butter over high heat until done. Remove.
Add remaining meat, mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until meat is done and onion is tender.
Return all meat to skillet.
Add sour cream mixture.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding as directed in blender or with hand mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.

title: little ham sandwiches
directions: Slice rolls in one continuous top; spread with mustard.
Layer ham and cheese on bottom; put together.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over the top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Slice and serve.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix thoroughly and sprinkle on top of souffle.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: colcannon
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small pieces. Cover with boiling water and cook until tender.
Drain and dry over low heat.
Mash and add 2 to 3 tablespoons of butter and the warm milk.
Beat until light and fluffy.

title: impossible pie
directions: Pour all ingredients in blender; mix very well, then pour mixture into a 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake, until custard is set, in oven at 400° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve cold.

title: 7-up orange cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the first 2 ingredients and cool.
Add the 7-Up. Chill in the refrigerator until thickened.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples.
Place on center of pastry square. Place 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 teaspoon oleo in each apple. Sprinkle each apple with cinnamon.
Bring opposite points of pastry up over apple.
Overlap; moisten and seal.
Carefully place a few inches apart in baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until well browned.
Serve warm with cream, if desired.

title: simply supreme chicken(5 minute preparation time: 2 hours cooking time)
directions: Separate breast layers and remove paper.
Place rice in bottom of 9-inch square casserole.
Stir in mushroom soup, water, mushrooms and liquid.
Top with frozen breasts.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 400°.
Remove cover.
Separate breasts and arrange skin side up.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover.
Return to oven and bake 1 hour longer or until tender.

title: hot, hot, hot sauce
directions: Puree peppers and garlic in a blender with 1/2 cup of the vinegar.
Put mixture in a saucepan with remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour into small, sterilized jars and seal.
This is very hot.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Pour flour, Parmesan cheese, pepper and salt into a large Ziploc freezer bag. Shake ingredients well. Cut potatoes into fourths or halves.
Add potatoes to the Ziploc bag and shake mixture well.
Place the potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt 1/2 cup margarine and pour over potatoes. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: food for angels
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Add sugar to egg whites.
Fold in crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in buttered 9 x 11-inch pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When cooled, spread 12 ounces Cool Whip on top.
Top with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter until tender.
Cook rice by box directions.
Also cook broccoli by box directions; drain and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, milk and melted butter together.
Sift remaining ingredients together to make a soft dough and add to sweet potato mixture.
Turn out on a floured board and toss lightly until outside looks smooth.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Bake on a greased baking sheet at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: ruth strickland's hardee style biscuits
directions: Whisk together water, egg, sour cream and sugar.
Add 1 cup Bisquick.
Whisk, then add 2 more cups Bisquick.
Put kneading hand into Bisquick and knead 6 to 8 times.
Use large cutter.
Makes 7 large biscuits.
Bake at 450° in an 8-inch pan.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients (except oil and tomato sauce) with hands in a large bowl.
When mixed, form 1 1/2 to 2-inch diameter balls. Fry in olive oil until browned and crusty on outside.
Put in tomato sauce and simmer 1 hour.

title: barbara armstrong's coffee cake
directions: Mix in order.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle sugar on top until it does not get damp from the batter, then add cinnamon to suit your taste.
Bake 20 minutes in 425° oven.
If you double the recipe, bake only 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Barbara says the secret to this cake staying moist is not overbaking.

title: angel's delight
directions: Prepare whipped topping according to package directions, set aside.
Tear cake into bite size pieces.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and peanut butter until crumbly; using 3/4 of this mixture, pat in bottom of pie crust.
Mix pudding with milk; pour over peanut butter mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remainder of peanut butter mixture on top.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Then add water and stir until its as thick as you want.

title: rancher's beans
directions: Coat medium saucepan with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add green pepper; saute 3 minutes. Add baked beans and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Contains about 125 calories per 1/2 cup serving.
Contains protein 6, fat 0.7, carbohydrates 2515, cholesterol 0, iron 2.2, sodium 494 and calcium 67.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Saute onion in oleo.
Combine all in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients, then add buttermilk.
Mix well, then add dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well, but don't overbeat.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt kathy's lu lu salad
directions: Mix together 1 1/4 cups hot water and lime gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Combine softened cream cheese and evaporated milk.
Add crushed pineapple and chopped walnuts.
Add to cooled gelatin mixture.
Stir well and chill.

title: salami roll-ups
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Roll out each slice with rolling pin. Place salami on bread and roll up.
Dip in beaten egg.
Place in buttered frying pan and fry until lightly browned.

title: 24 hour luncheon salad
directions: Put eggs in double boiler, add vinegar and sugar, beating constantly and cook until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat; add butter and let cool.
Mix fruit and marshmallows together with cooled, cooked mixture.
Let set for 24 hours.
Maraschino cherries can be added for color.
It can be put in freezer.

title: spinach scalloped franks
directions: Saute onions in shortening.
Add flour and make a paste. Slowly mix in milk to prevent lumping.
Heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in 3/4 cup cheese until melted.
Add spinach.
Layer twice in casserole potatoes, franks and sauce.
Bake, covered, 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven. Uncover and melt reserved 1/4 cup cheese on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: irish potatoes(candy)
directions: In a large bowl, place coconut and confectioners sugar and mix.
Add lite cream, but only until you can form a ball (1/2-inch in diameter).
Roll in cinnamon.
Makes 30 to 35 candy potatoes.

title: jib vi rum punch
directions: Fill tall glass with ice.
Add Appleton's or any dark rum.
Add grenadine and whiskey sour mix.
Fill glass almost to top with orange juice.
Shake and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange peaches on bottom of dish.
Mix flour and 1 cup sugar together; sprinkle over peaches.
Dot with butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Mix the Bisquick, 1/4 cup sugar, egg and enough milk to make 1/2 cup.
Add the 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Drop on peach mixture and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and let cool.
Crumble half of cake in bottom of clear punch bowl.
Mix pudding with 5 cups milk.
Layer half of pudding on top of crumbled cake.
Add a layer of 1 can pie filling, 1 can pineapple, 1 container Cool Whip and 1/2 cup nuts. Repeat until all ingredients are used.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients of batter and put in a pan.

title: holiday nut cookies
directions: Cream oleo, shortening and sugar.
Blend in water and vanilla. Add flour and nuts.
Roll out on floured board and cut into desired shapes or can be rolled into log shape, chilled and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes until lightly brown.
When slightly cool, coat with powdered sugar.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cranapple nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three loaf pans. Prepare fruits and nuts; set aside.

title: pineapple cheese dip
directions: Mix together at room temperature; chill.

title: stuffed green pepper
directions: Mix all but peppers (chop tomatoes in blender).
Clean and halve peppers.
Fill peppers and place in covered pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave pecan rolls
directions: Layer bottom of an 8-inch microwave dish with pecans and sprinkle brown sugar over pecans; pour 1/4 cup of the melted margarine over sugar and pecans.
Cut biscuits into quarters and layer on top of mixture in pan.
Pour the other 1/4 cup of margarine over top.
Cook on High for 5 minutes.
If more time is needed, cook at 1 minute intervals.

title: no drip ice pops
directions: Combine boiling water and gelatin in a blender until gelatin is dissolved. Blend in banana until smooth, then blend in yogurt. Pour mixture into popsicle molds or little cups until hard. (If pouring into little cups, insert sticks when firm, then continue freezing until hard.)

title: black bottom pie
directions: Mix gingersnaps with melted butter and press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in 500° oven for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Add egg yolks gradually to hot milk.
Combine cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar and stir into the milk mixture.
Cool for 20 minutes, stirring constantly until it coats spoon.
Chill.
Remove and take out 1 cup of the mixture to which you add the bitter chocolate squares and beat well as it cools.
Add vanilla.
Pour this into the gingersnap crust and chill.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to the remaining hot custard and cool.
Beat egg whites; when stiff, add 1/2 cup sugar and cream of tartar and bourbon.
Fold into the plain custard mixture and pour on top of the chocolate mixture.
Chill. Cover top of pie with whipping cream, whipped with shavings of bitter chocolate.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: herman's hermits
directions: Mix.
Press into jelly roll pan or a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Cut and enjoy!

title: cajun dove recipe
directions: Dry dove with paper towel and rub with salt and pepper.
Heat 2 to 4 tablespoons oil (depending on number of doves) in pot and saute slowly until light brown.
Add 2 to 3 cups water; cover with a tight lid and simmer until tender.
Then add juice of 1 lemon, 1/4 cup chopped parsley, 1 pod of hot pepper and large lump of butter.
Simmer another 15 minutes.
Serve on toast.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl beat Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork with sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: granny raysick's banana cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add bananas and sour cream or yogurt.
Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add and mix to make batter.
Grease and flour 9-inch tube pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 45 minutes).
Cook in pan 5 minutes, then turn out on rack.

title: hamburger pie
directions: You will need 1 (9-inch) dish or baking pan.

title: roasted red peppers and mushroom sauce for pasta
directions: Combine ingredients and saute for 40 minutes.
Cook as you would prepare clam sauce.
Boil pasta, add sauce and fresh grated Asiago cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Makes enough sauce for 15 people.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Peel the potatoes and slice thin.
Oil a rectangular baking dish.
Arrange some of the potato slices on the bottom.
Sprinkle very lightly with a bit of flour.
Add salt and pepper to taste; sprinkle on some of the parsley.
Repeat, making 2 or 3 more layers.
Meanwhile heat the butter and milk together in a small saucepan over low heat; pour over the potatoes.
Top with paprika.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until a nice golden brown crust forms on the top and the potatoes are tender.

title: dessert crepes
directions: Mix together.
Batter should be thin.
Use a small, nonstick frypan on medium heat.
Lightly butter.
Pour scant 1/4 cup of batter in center.
Rotate pan until it quits running.
Flip when dry on edges.
Repeat.
Use immediately or stack with pieces of wax paper between crepes.
(Can be frozen for later use.)
Fill.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Beat together next 3 ingredients and spread over cold crust.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water, then add frozen strawberries.
Chill until it starts to set, then pour over cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot.
Keep heated for serving.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add spices to taste.
Boil manicotti (add a little shortening so noodles won't stick).
Mix cheese, bread crumbs and eggs to meat mixture, blend well and stuff noodles.
Put in a greased dish and cover with sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Beat eggs with salt until stiff.
Gradually add sugar, beating until very stiff.
Add vanilla and almond; fold in nuts.

title: shrimp muffin spread
directions: Mix altogether and spread on English muffins and toast under broiler until brown and bubbly.
Can be made ahead if spread on muffins and then frozen.
Just put under broiler when ready to use as they thaw quickly.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Lay one can of crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Beat cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Spread on top of rolls.
Add other can of crescent rolls to top.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in angel food cake pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Slice carrots and cut elephant into bite-size pieces (this takes about 3 months).
Add enough gravy to cover meat.
(Be prepared to go through several "hand can openers".) Cook over kerosene fire for 4 to 5 weeks at 465°.
This will serve approximately 3,800 people.
If more come to dinner than expected, the 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people don't like hare in their stew!

title: bean salad
directions: Chop bell pepper and onion, add pimento and beans.
Bring to a boil sugar, oil and wine vinegar.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour in heavy pan.
Beat egg yolks and mix into pan.
Stir on medium heat.
Stir in dry ingredients, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Layer wafers and bananas in glass baking dish.
Pour pudding over layers.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Steam until tender; drain.
Blend soup, mayonnaise, beaten egg, onion and cheese. Fold cooked and drained eggplant into this mixture.
Put in buttered dish and top with Ritz crackers or Pepperidge stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nongreasy cracklin corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add enough buttermilk to make a thin batter.
Pour into a 9-inch greased iron skillet.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and egg in medium bowl.
Beat until creamy.
Mix in flour and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: lasagna - sauceless
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and onion in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add garlic, mushroom pieces, bay leaf, salt, pepper, spices and tomato paste.
Rinse each tomato paste can with 3 tablespoons water; stir into meat mixture.
Simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Alternate layers of lasagna, meat sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses in greased oblong baking dish. Repeat layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mixed vegetables and mushrooms
directions: *You can substitute 1/2 teaspoon garlic pepper for these two spices, if you prefer.

title: fudgie scotch squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Press mixture into very well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Easier to get out if removed when still warm.

title: cherry crumble
directions: Put pineapple and cherry pie filling in 8 x 10-inch pan.
Add 1 box yellow cake mix on top of pineapple-cherry mixture.
Top with pecans, coconut, and butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Place bread cubes and raisins in greased 8 X 8 baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over bread cubes.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together. Mix 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Mix with onion and pimento.
Make dressing out of remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10.

title: cool whip treat
directions: Mix 2 cups of the cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup of the sugar and margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly into the bottom of pan and refrigerate.

title: italian beef for sandwiches
directions: Cook on low heat (325°) for 4 hours.
Remove from heat. Take meat out
of
juice
to
cool
and	slice.	Place back in juice. (If chuck
roast is used, remove fat and take apart in small pieces.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil butter and corn syrup gently for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs gently, not until frothy.
Mix pecans, salt, sugar and vanilla with eggs.
Pour syrup mixture over egg mixture and blend.
Place in pie crust. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for 25 minutes more, until center no longer shakes.
Do not overbake. Pie will firm up as it cools.

title: how to bake a cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pans).
Grease pans generously and dust with flour.
Blend in large bowl at low speed until moistened: cake mix, water, eggs and oil.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed or 450 strokes by hand.
Pour batter into pan(s). Bake until done.
Cake is done if toothhpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Do not test for doneness by touching with finger.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Spray a large oval casserole with Pam.
Roll out one crust and place in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle sugar over blueberries in pan. Sprinkle flour and lemon juice over sugar.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Roll out second pie crust and place on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the crumbs and pour into a well buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: cocoa kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, mixing well.
Add flour, cocoa and baking powder; stir in walnuts.
Chill dough 2 hours.

title: chicken caesar
directions: To make Caesar Dressing, place first 7 ingredients in food processor, processing until smooth and creamy.
Add salt to taste.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Mix dry jello with pineapple (undrained).
Stir in cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: crab quiche
directions: Lightly bake pie crust shell approximately 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs until blended, then stir in cream, onion, salt and cayenne pepper.
Pat crab meat dry.
Sprinkle crab and cheese in pie crust shell.
Pour egg mixture over and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce temperature to 300° and bake 20 minutes longer, or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Let rest 10 minutes before cutting into 8 wedges.
Each serving is approximately 370 calories, 221 mg cholesterol, 31 g fat and 715 mg sodium.

title: pane di spagna
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Gradually add sugar and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to eggs and sugar; mix well. Add vanilla continuously beating.
Pour into a greased tube pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and spices together.
Make a hole in flour and put oil, egg yolks and stiffly beaten egg whites in.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Break cookies in good size pieces.
Save some for the top of the cake.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and cheese together; set aside.
Butter bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer half broccoli, half chicken and 1/2 soup mixture.
Repeat layers with remaining.
Top with bread crumbs (optional).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: leftover chicken and noodles
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup and milk; stir in chicken, noodles, corn, peas, onion, pepper and paprika.
Top with crumbs. Cook for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Add buttermilk to yeast mixture and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk mixture and mix until all ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out on floured board and knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with a 2-inch cutter.
Place on lightly greased pans.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: beefed-up biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and chilies; drain.
Stir tomato sauce, chili and garlic powders; simmer while preparing dough. Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits (pull each one in 2 layers).
Put 10 layers in ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan. Combine 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and egg.
Mix well.
Remove meat from heat and stir in sour cream mixture; spoon over dough. Arrange remaining biscuits over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 357° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Put in bottom of casserole.
Boil chicken one hour, cut up and put over broccoli.
Add soups, mayonnaise and milk.
Put cheese on top and croutons.
Drizzle margarine over all.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan; in a large bowl combine all ingredients with a spoon, just until mixed well.
Pour into pan; bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chili pie
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with chips.
Spoon chili evenly over chips, then add another layer of chips.
Bake or microwave until chili bubbles.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts. Serve hot.

title: pie crust(makes 4 single pie crusts)
directions: Mix altogether.
Roll out.
Put in pie tins and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: praise the lord cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes. Make pudding by directions; cool.
Pour pineapple mixture over baked cake; cool.
Arrange slices of banana over mixture; then spread pudding evenly.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda, salt, cocoa and egg.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Beat together.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Leave room for spreading.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Put together with filling.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Stir in sugar.
Add dates.
Stir until mixture leaves the sides of pan.
Stir in milk.
Add well beaten eggs and salt.
Cook 2 minutes and then remove from heat. Add vanilla, 4 cups Rice Krispies and 1 cup nuts.
When cool enough to handle, roll out into walnut size balls.
Roll into coconut.
These freeze well.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper.
Drain off grease.
Mix the soups, pimentos and rice.
Add sausage mixture to soup mixture.
Mix well.
Top with cheese (optional).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Place sauerkraut in colander; rinse with cold water.
Drain well.
Combine sauerkraut, onion, celery, green pepper and pimentos in a large bowl; mix well.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In bowl, blend cake mix, apple, 1/3 cup apple butter, yogurt and egg whites. Beat 2 minutes on high.
Evenly sprinkle nut mixture alternating with batter in Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch pan (spray pan with Pam before putting batter in it).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Blend powdered sugar and 2 to 3 tablespoons apple butter and spoon over cake.
Makes 20 servings.

title: crunchy top pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well beaten. Fold in flour.
Grease and flour tube pan. Pour in batter and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: pecan pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into two 9-inch pie crusts. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and stir.
Cover and place over low heat until cream cheese softens.
Place crab dip in dish.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In skillet in hot oil, saute celery and onion until soft and tender-crisp.
Combine soup and milk.
Add all ingredients together and stir until completely mixed.
Pour into 10 x 6-inch baking dish or casserole dish and microwave until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Soak the pecans for several hours in 1 quart of water containing 1 tablespoon of salt.
Most of the pecan shells will crack in your hands, leaving the meats intact.

title: chili cornbread
directions: Stir together corn meal, baking powder, salt, eggs, corn, butter and sour cream. With a spoon, beat until combined.
Stir in cheese and chilies. Turn into an 8-inch square glass baking dish and bake in preheated 350° oven until a cake tester comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: super slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, celery, apple, raisins and walnuts.
In a smaller bowl, mix the mayonnaise, milk, salt, sugar, pepper and vinegar.
Pour dressing over the contents of the large bowl and mix gently.
Serve when ready.

title: old english caramel apples
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugars and cornstarch.
Stir in half and half.
Add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil (6 to 10 minutes). Boil 1 minute.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Let cool 16 minutes. Meanwhile, core and chunk apples and place in 6 individual bowls. Serve about 1/2 cup warm sauce over each serving of apples. Yield:
6 servings (1 3/4 cups sauce).

title: toad in the hole
directions: In a medium bowl combine first 6 ingredients; beat until smooth and creamy.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 425°. In a 10-inch dish, arrange sausages in a spoke-like fashion.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Fold 1/2 cup cheese into the batter.
Spoon mixture over sausages and top with apples.
Let bake for 20 minutes or until puffy and golden.
Top with remaining cheese and bake until just melted.
Serve with maple syrup or apple butter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: savory squash
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash. Saute onion and celery in butter. Add all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, brown beef.
Drain off fat.
Stir in soups, water, vegetables and Worcestershire. Mix well.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Cut biscuits into fourths. Remove dish from oven; stir.
Arrange biscuits on top; top with cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes or until biscuits are brown. Serves 6.
Prep time:
15 minutes.
Cook time:
20 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken in 1 1/2-inch strips.
Put oil in wok.
Add chicken and soy sauce; brown chicken and remove.
Add onion, peppers, cabbage and frozen vegetables to wok.
After these have cooked until crisp-tender, add chicken.
Drain water chestnuts and mushrooms (reserving liquids) and add to wok.
Mix cornstarch with reserved liquid and add to mixture; cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Cook rice according to directions on package and serve with this stir-fry.

title: nutri-grain pie crust
directions: Place Nutri-Grain flakes in plastic bag and crush lightly with rolling pin.
Stir in all ingredients, making sure pineapple concentrate is mixed evenly.
Spray a 9-inch pie pan with nonstick spray and pour mixture into pan.
Press pie crust into place with a rubber spatula or your hands.
Bake at 400° for about 7 minutes or until golden brown.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Lace ribs on spit accordion style and secure with holding forks.
Adjust on rotisserie above drip pan.
Let ribs rotate over slow coals.
In a saucepan, cook onions in hot oil until tender. Add remaining ingredients; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
After ribs cook 40 minutes, baste well with sauce.
Add damp hickory to coals.
Cook 20 minutes longer or until well done.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Place grated cabbage in bowl; add grated bell pepper and onion.
Do not stir.
Place remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Don't stir.
Cover the bowl and place in refrigerator overnight.
Stir just before serving.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat all ingredients, except walnuts.
Shape into a ball and roll in walnuts.
Wrap with waxed paper.
Chill.

title: round steak with rich gravy
directions: Cut steak into 5 or 6 pieces.
Place in slow cooking pot. Add dry onion soup mix, water and mushroom soup.
Cover; cook on low temperature for 6 to 8 hours.

title: crawfish etouffee(serves 6)
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add tails and saute for 5 minutes. Add soup and V-8 juice.
Season to taste with Tabasco, pepper and salt or Tony Chachere seasoning).
Cook for 20 minutes on low. Serve over rice.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain and add enchilada sauce. Mix soups with water. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer, starting with tortilla chips.
Add hamburger mixture, soup mixture and cheese.
End with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as package directs, stir in apples.

Pour in baking dish and bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. In medium bowl, combine sweetened milk, sour cream and lemon juice. Remove cake from oven and spread cream mixture over top.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle with cinnamon; cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg, salt and sugar.
Add vanilla and milk; beat thoroughly.
Pour into glass and sprinkle lightly with nutmeg. Serves 1.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Stir in mandarin oranges.
Bake cake in 2 or 3 layer pans, following package directions.
Cool.

title: chicken soup supreme
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
After cooking, remove skin and bone.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch chunks.
Boil eggs; after boiling, dice eggs.
Dice onion.
Add these ingredients to cream of chicken soup (prepared with water as directed on soup can). When mixture comes to a boil it is ready to serve.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine soup and milk.
In shallow casserole, arrange broccoli and chicken.
Top with soup mixture and buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or microwave, covered, on High for 6 minutes, rotating halfway through heating.

title: 7-up cake
directions: To mix, cream sugar and shortening together and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured mold Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: mock caesar salad
directions: Put the garlic, soy sauce and lemon juice in a salad bowl and whisk thoroughly.
Add the endive and romaine lettuce.
Toss to coat.
Sprinkle the black pepper and Parmesan cheese on top. Garnish with the chopped tomato.
Serves 4.
Contains 1.2 grams fat per serving and 80 calories.

title: banana split pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine milk, sour cream, 1/4 cup lemon juice and vanilla; mix well.
Chill.

title: chocolate nut zucchini cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling, water or in microwave. Let cool.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Sift flour, powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat eggs at high speed until thick and light.
Gradually add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, beating well.
Add salad oil and cooled chocolate, beat until well blended.
At low speed, add sifted dry ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Add grated zucchini and nuts with wooden spoon.
Stir until well combined. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Freezes well and is delicious.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt and cornstarch in medium sauce pan. Mix milk and egg yolks together. Gradually blend in dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Cook on medium heat until thick. Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla. Pour into 9 inch crust. Top with meringue.

title: individual meat loaves
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cilantro naan(indian tortilla)
directions: Mix all the ingredient and make a dough.
Cover and let stand for 15 min.
Divide the dough in small ball.
Heat a pan on medium heat.
Roll out the balls in circle using flour if needed (like you are making a small pizza crust).
Take the rolled crust and place it on the pan.
Cook until its lightly brown.
Flip it and let it cook on the other side until lightly brown.
Put a tsp of oil and flip it.
Let it cook until done.
Do the same thing on the other side.
Enjoy with soup, curries, or casserole.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; roll balls in mixture to coat. Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: red christmas cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and continue beating hard.
Make a paste of coloring and cocoa.
Add paste to mixture and continue beating hard.
Add salt and flour alternately with buttermilk.
Continue to beat hard.
Add vanilla and beat more.
Add vinegar to soda and then blend into mixture (do not beat, just blend).
Pour into 2 or 3 greased and floured standard cake pans.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: braised cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into pieces, removing tough inner core.
In a covered pan, simmer cabbage in stock, about 20 minutes or until tender.
Uncover and continue cooking until liquid boils away. Add butter, salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: 1 bowl - 1 hour rolls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in fairly large bowl.
Stir in flour. Let rise until doubled, then make into rolls using more flour and kneading with hands.
Put into well-greased pan or pans and let rise until doubled.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Place crushed pineapple on bottom of an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over the pineapple, then pour cake mix over cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: liver dumpling soup
directions: Soak bread in milk and squeeze dry.
Crumble into ground liver.
Add other ingredients.
Add enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Drop dumplings in boiling beef broth.
Cook slow for 20 to 30 minutes, then serve as soup.
You can also add carrots while you are cooking the broth.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in pan.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork and mushroom stew
directions: In a large saucepan, brown pork, half at a time, in olive oil. Return all meat to pan.
Stir in chicken broth, wine, parsley, thyme, garlic powder, pepper and bay leaf.
Simmer, covered, for 40 minutes.
Add frozen onions, carrots and mushrooms.
Simmer another 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Combine cold water and cornstarch.
Add to stew with lemon juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, raisins and onion in large bowl. Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in another bowl and pour over mixture.
Stir well.
Let set for at least 1 hour.
Stir well again before serving.

title: sausage-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and pull out stems. Fill mushrooms with raw sausage; pat until sausage is mounded. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes, or until sausage looks well browned. The last 5 minutes of baking, top mushrooms with shredded cheese.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix rest of ingredients except nuts thoroughly. Shape into ball and roll in nuts.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforated sides together to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture along center of dough in log shape.
Fold sides over center, then ends.
Use fork to press and seal ends.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Each 8 ounce can of Pillsbury crescent rolls makes 4.

title: turkey or chicken apple salad
directions: In medium bowl gently stir together turkey or chicken, apples, celery and raisins.
In cup stir together dressing and brown sugar. Pour over turkey mixture.
Toss lightly to coat.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 1 1/2 cups or 2 servings.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, vegetable oil and sugar until light and fluffy. Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk to which flavorings have been added.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or a little longer if needed.
Freezes well.

title: ham and cheese stromboli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Roll bread dough into a 15 x 10 inch rectangle. Sprinkle with broccoli, cheese and ham to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Tuck ends of bread dough and fold top over.
Pinch to seal.
Brush top of bread with melted margarine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on a foil-lined cookie sheet sprayed with non-stick coating.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat milk in a saucepan with 2 egg yolks.
When hot, add sugar and flour mixed together to milk and egg yolks.
Stir and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add coconut and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into cookie pie shell.
Add meringue.

title: granny's caramel nut slices
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in flour, salt and soda last.
Then add nuts.
Form into rolls (about 4) and chill overnight.
Slice in 1/8-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 dozen.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Mix soups, milk and wine.
Put aside.
Put about 1 tablespoon of oil in the bottom of a large casserole dish.
Place raw rice in bottom of pan (and seasoning packet).
Pour half of sauce mixture over rice.
Place chicken on rice; season with salt and pepper. Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours or slightly more.
(Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top before baking, if desired.)

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Place cooked and drained carrots in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Blend soup and cheese.
Pour over carrots.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Slice onion.
Pull apart flowerets from cauliflower.
Shred lettuce.
Make 3 layers of onion, bacon, cauliflower and lettuce.
Then mix together the mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese for dressing; spread over the top of the salad.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving, then mix just prior to serving.

title: spaghetti chicken tetrazzini
directions: Make a white sauce of the butter, flour and salt.
Add the chicken broth, sherry or brandy flavoring, Parmesan cheese and whipping cream.
Cook the spaghetti. Cook the chicken, cool and cube.
Put cooked spaghetti in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread cooked chicken over spaghetti. Spread the mushrooms over the chicken. Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour (uncovered).

title: spaghetti squash casserole
directions: Place the spaghetti squash in a large pot of water (it should float) and bring to a boil. Lower heat. Cover and boil gently for 50 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake cornbread and set aside to cool.
Then crumble coarsely. Cook bacon crisp and cool.
Finely chop bell pepper.
Chop eggs. Grate or finely chop onion.
Crumble cooked bacon; add this to cornbread with 1 cup mayonnaise.
Gently add finely chopped tomatoes.
Mix well and refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Crumble the pretzels in the
bottom of an oblong baking dish. Pour oleo and 3
tablespoons
sugar
over
pretzels and mix.
Bake at 350° for 8 to
10 minutes.
Cool.
(Make sure to use a spatula to scrape up
from
the
bottom
after it cools, otherwise it would be difficult to
spoon
from
the
pan.)
I usually refrigerate it.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix together well in punch bowl or pitcher. Add 5 c. crushed ice. Add pineapple sherbet, if desired.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar and egg together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately to egg mixture with molasses and hot water mixture.
Pour into a greased waxed paper lined 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Delicious treat served with whipped cream and grated cheese.

title: "quiche"
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in the middle comes clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup and broth together and put in casserole pan. Cook stuffing according to directions and cover chicken mixture with it.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
If it appears to be getting too brown, cover with foil for 1/2 of the baking time.

title: chocolate pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour 1/4 cup batter on hot griddle. Cook pancakes until puffed.
Turn and cook other sides until golden brown.
Dust with powdered sugar. "Tastes just like a chocolate donut." Christine Walsh.

title: neiman-marcus cookie bars
directions: Blend cake mix, egg and oleo with fork or pastry cutter.
Cream together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs.
Put cake mix mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, beaten egg and 1/2 can tomato sauce. Form into loaf and put in shallow pan.
Combine remaining sauce with other ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: snow-topped thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat the first 4 ingredients until smooth. Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Chill 10 minutes.
Roll into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press center of each with thumb; fill with preserves.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes, or until edges are golden.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Store loosely covered.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together; add to first mixture and mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for about 45 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven, turn oven off and spread marshmallows over top of cake; return to oven for 10 minutes or until marshmallows melt.
Cool, then ice.

title: cheeseroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
In a large skillet, brown meat with chopped onion. Add soups, green pepper, pimento and cooked macaroni; mix.
Place half of the mixture in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with half of the cheese and half of the French fried onions. Top with remaining macaroni mixture, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with remaining French fried onions and bake 5 minutes longer. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork chop chow mein
directions: Cook pork chops in small amount of fat; do not brown.
Cut cooked chops into small pieces.
Add celery and onions and saute. Put in heavy pot and add the rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil and add 3 tablespoons cornstarch, dissolved in 1 cup boiling water.
Cook about 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice and sprinkle with Chinese noodles.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, milk and salt in a large saucepan. Cook and stir on medium heat until thickened. Beat eggs lightly with wire whisk.
Add a little hot mixture to eggs and blend well. Pour eggs into mixture in saucepan.
Cook and stir for a few minutes. Add butter flavor Crisco and vanilla. Blend mixture well. Cool slightly. Cover surface of pudding with plastic wrap.
Place layer of wafers on bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Alternate with layers of banana and pudding, ending with pudding on top. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix meat with eggs, bread, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, catsup and 1/4 cup water.
Roll into 1-inch balls and brown in oil.
In a separate pan, melt jelly with chili sauce and water from chili bottle (see note).
Add browned meat balls to chili sauce.
Cook over low heat for 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice for a main dish or use as an appetizer.
May be frozen.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix butter and sauce.
Mix salt, corn meal and pepper thoroughly. Soak fish in liquid mix.
Roll in dry mix until completely covered.
Fry in hot skillet until golden brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Stir; simmer for 1 hour. Stir frequently.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and cook 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Do not overcook or it will get too hard.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening together until like meal.
In a small bowl, mix water, vinegar and egg together, then add to mixture.
Mix and roll out on floured board.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, beat eggs. Add butter, coconut, milk and vanilla. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wild rice and sausage
directions: Combine sausage, celery, onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until sausage is browned and vegetables are tender. Stir to crumble meat.
Drain.
Stir in rest of items, except almonds.
Mix well.
Put in greased 3 quart casserole and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Make pudding according to package directions.
In large bowl, crumble 1/3 of cake.
Add 1/3 of pie filling, pudding and Cool Whip.
Alternate each layer until the Cool Whip is final layer on top.
Chill 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: seven layer dinner(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Using 2 to 3-quart casserole, layer hamburg on bottom, then rice, celery, carrots, onions and potatoes.
Pour tomatoes on top. Salt and pepper every other layer.
Bake, covered, in slow oven at 275° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: easy pina colada bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press crust mix into greased pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: dressed-up meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients.
Press into loaf dish, 9 x 5-inch or 9-inch round baking dish with inverted custard cup in center.
Microwave at High until internal temperature reaches 150° for 11 to 15 minutes.
Rotate once or twice during cooking.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, melt shortening.
Add chopped onion and continue cooking until lightly browned.
Lower heat and add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Delicious over chicken, bake at 400° for 1 hour (covered) or ribs, bake at 400° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (covered).

title: chicken souffle
directions: Boil chicken until tender, debone.
Place meat in bottom of large flat pan; set aside.
In large saucepan, put soups, milk, broth and margarine.
Bring to boiling point.
Remove from heat. Add bread slices and let set for a few minutes.
Mash up bread, add onion powder and eggs (beaten).
Mix well, add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until light brown.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust:
Pat flat crescent rolls into a large cookie sheet. Bake according to directions on package or until golden brown. Cool.

title: macaroni and ground beef goulash
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Cook macaroni by package directions and drain thoroughly.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to macaroni and cook 20 minutes.
Add meat mixture.
Toss together and serve while hot.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In a 2-quart baking dish, combine sausage, sauce, noodles, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese, mixing well.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until heated through.

title: old time gingerbread cookies
directions: Stir together flour, ginger, cinnamon, soda, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
In saucepan melt shortening.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Beat in sugar and molasses.
Then beat in eggs.
In large mixing bowl beat together the molasses mixture and 1/2 flour mixture.
Then gradually add rest of flour mixture.
Chill dough for about 1 hour.
Then on floured surface roll out dough about 1/2 at a time to about 1/4 inch.
Then, cut with cookie cutter (you can sprinkle with additional sugar if you like).
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are golden.
Cool, then frost if you like.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: apple pie (loaf bread topping)
directions: Place apples in baking dish. Trim bread. Cut in strips and place on top of apples. Mix margarine, flour, sugar and beaten eggs.
Dribble over bread and let set for 15 minutes. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: crock pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all together and put in crock pot that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle some cheese on top and cook 3 hour on low.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth.
Put in pie crusts.
Melt butter in pan.
Add coconut and almonds; stir.
Put on cookie sheet and place in a 350° oven until toasted.
Put coconut and almond topping on pies.
Pour 1/2 jar butterscotch topping on each pie.
Freeze.

title: italian cheese balls
directions: Mix together and form 2 balls.
Can roll in chopped pecans. Chill before serving.

title: west virginia apple black walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples and sugar and set aside (let stand).
Beat eggs slightly.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat together; add apples, sugar and walnuts to batter.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 hour.

title: mrs. harter's icing
directions: Mix together egg whites and granulated sugar.
Beat over double boiler until thick and foamy (150°).
Cool.
Add Crisco, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: antipasto
directions: Cook first 6

ingredients, stirring constantly to rapid boil. Add cut green peppers and cook 10 minutes. Next, add pickling onions (drained), pitted black olives (drained) and salad or Spanish olives. Last, add mushrooms, tuna and cauliflower, which was pre-cooked in salted water.

title: west virginia mud cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until thick and lemon color. Blend in drained pineapple.
Fold prepared Dream Whip mixture into creamed mixture.
Using 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan, make alternate layers of graham cracker crumbs and the Dream Whip mixture, starting with the crumbs.
Chill for 6 or more hours.
You may use Cool Whip to save time (large size).

title: champagne punch
directions: Pour 1 bottle of ginger ale and lemonade concentrate into an 11-cup ring mold; add cherries and freeze until firm.
Unmold ice ring in a punch bowl; add remaining ginger ale, orange juice and champagne.
Stir well.
Yield: 18 cups.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole with browned hamburger.
Cover meat with mixed vegetables.
Cover with soup; rinse can with small amount of water.
Lay cheese on top of soup.
Top with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: patrick's favorite cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until well mixed.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook, skin, debone and chop chicken.
Place in casserole dish. Mix together soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Melt oleo and mix with crushed crackers and poppy seed.
Top casserole with crackers, oleo and poppy seed mixture.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until crackers are toasted and casserole is hot and bubbly through and through.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugars
and
cinnamon
together in small bowl.
Cut each biscuit into
4 pieces and roll in sugar mixture to coat. Drop into a
greased
Bundt
pan.
Be
sure
to	use all sugar mixture. Melt
oleo
and
pour over biscuits; stir lightly to mix.	Bake at	350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out onto platter and serve.

title: bob evans country ribs
directions: Wipe the spareribs with a damp cloth and cut into sections of 4 or 5 ribs each. Sprinkle each piece generously with meat tenderizer and let set for about 10 minutes. Place in a deep pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil and simmer gently for about 20 to 25 minutes until tender, or use a pressure cooker and cook until tender. Drain. Let ribs cool and marinate with Barbecue Sauce. Refrigerate overnight. Bake the next day in a slow oven, 325° to 350°, about 1 hour or until brown in a shallow baking pan. Add more sauce for extra flavor.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Turn oven to 225°.
When it reaches that temperature turn it off.
Put chocolate in Pyrex dish and place in oven to melt, about l5-20 minutes or longer.
Mix in all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Allow to harden.

title: marshmallow-cereal bars
directions: Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches or rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Place margarine and marshmallows in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave uncovered on High, 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring after 1 minute until mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
Press mixture in pan, using buttered back of spoon.
Cool.
Makes 16 or 24 bars.

title: "torrijas"
directions: Cook the milk with 1 stick cinnamon and 1 pound sugar 3 minutes; leave until cold.
Beat the eggs well in other receptacle.
Wet each bread slice in the milk.
After that, wrap up in the beaten eggs.
Fry in very hot oil.
Put them on a tray and sprinkle with the sugar and ground cinnamon (half and half). Leave until cold.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti by box directions. Drain.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: salmon or tuna almondine
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water and let stand for 1 minute.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
With a wire whip or electric beater, blend in the cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Fold in green onion, pimientos, tuna or salmon and 1/2 c. almonds.	Turn into a 5 1/2 c. mold or bowl and chill until firm.
To serve unmold onto a platter, garnish with almonds, overlapping the slices to form scales and if desired garnish with green olives sliced or parsley.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: marcy's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir soda into buttermilk and add, alternating with flour.
Add flavorings and salt.
Cut wax paper to fit bottom of tube pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat all together and add scalded milk.
Pour into crust and bake 5 minutes at 475°, and then 20 or 30 minutes at 425°.

title: beef and noodle medley
directions: In large skillet, brown meat in oil, about 5 minutes.
Add celery, onion and green pepper; saute 5 minutes longer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until noodles are tender, about 20 minutes.
Can add cooked leftover vegetables, such as peas, green beans, carrots, cabbage, etc.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 of cheese and onion rings. Place in casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes with lid on.
Take off lid and sprinkle top with remaining cheese and can of fried onion rings.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Blend together dry ingredients. Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla for 1 1/2 minutes. Add bananas, sour cream, nuts and flour mixture and beat until well blended. Pour into greased pans; 3 small or one 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, until tests done. Turn out of pan and cool on wire rack.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Beat eggs and salt together separately, then add.
Add oil and vanilla.
Sift remaining ingredients together and add to mixture.
With a small spoon, take pieces of dough, the size of a walnut, roll into a ball and place an inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Put 1/2 cup of granulated, colored sugar in a small dish, dip end of tumbler into granules and press onto cookie (unbaked).
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: wild rice and chicken bake
directions: Place uncooked rice and half of the flavor packet (about 1 1/2 tablespoon) in a 3-quart rectangular baking dish.
Stir in water, soup, water chestnuts, frozen peas and carrots.
Arrange chicken over rice.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika and pepper.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven about 50 minutes or until chicken and rice are tender.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 6 main dish servings (150 calories per serving, 4 g total fat per serving).
tags: quick-cooking long grain and wild rice

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Prepare noodles as directed.
In small bowl, mix flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir in small amount of mushroom liquid until creamy.
Cook onion in butter for about 5 minutes.
Add meat and cook until done.
Add mushrooms and liquid, then add flour mixture.
Stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: In top of double boiler, over hot, but not boiling water, melt chocolate.
Add sweetened condensed milk; continue to cook over hot water for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in water. Remove from heat.
Pour mixture into large bowl.
Stir in vanilla. Cool.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a gallon container.
Yield: One gallon.

title: chicken mushroom soup
directions: Combine broth, celery and onion.
Cook until tender, then add mushrooms and chicken. Boil about 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and sauce.
Add eggs gradually and cook until firm.
Serve at once.
Serve hot.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together; let set 2 hours to mix flavors.
Dip in celery, carrots, cauliflower, radish or any other raw vegetable that you like.

title: meatballs in mustard sauce
directions: Mix ground beef with onion, bread crumbs, milk, egg, parsley, thyme, garlic, salt and pepper; shape mixture into meatballs. Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add half of the meatballs; cook over low heat until brown.
Repeat with other half of the meatballs over low heat.
Add the flour to the leftover fat in skillet and stir.
Add chicken broth a little at a time.
Cook, stirring, until it thickens.
Add cream, mustard and green onions. Add meatballs to sauce.
Serve with egg noodles.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys in first clause Proverbs 23:14 and you will have a good cake.

title: baked fish
directions: Remove fins from fish, clean carefully, wash and dry.
Place in dish, pour water and lemon juice over fish.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, onion and bread crumbs over fish.
Drop pieces of butter on fish.
Bake 30 minutes in preheated oven at 400° (depending on size of fish).

title: link sausage with apples
directions: Cover sausage with cold water.
Heat to boiling, drain.
Place sausage in large baking dish.
Cover with peeled sweet potatoes and onions. Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for one hour.
Uncover.
Add apples which have been pared, cored and halved.
Cover.
Bake slowly until fruit is tender. Serve at once.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Wash fruit fruit and chop; place in bowl.
Add 4 tablespoons of water and sugar to taste.
Mix all together and allow to chill 1 1/2 hours.
Serve either in bowls or shortbread cups.

title: impossible ham salad pie
directions: Layer peas, ham, cheese and onion.
Beat remaining ingredients; pour over.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pork 'n pepper stir-fry
directions: Slice about a pound of boneless pork loin into strips and stir-fry with vegetable oil, red and green pepper strips and crushed garlic.
Serve over hot, cooked rice with soy sauce or sweet and sour sauce.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, sausage, oats, onion, parsley, eggs, basil, salt, pepper and vegetable juice.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour. Shape into loaf and arrange bacon slices on top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then lower to 350°.
Add potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add salt, pepper and taco sauce.
Add soups and chilies to meat mixture.
Put layer of Doritos chips in casserole.
Add layer of meat mixture.
Add layer of cheese.
Alternate in this order, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Slice bananas and line the baked pie shell.
Reserve one sliced banana for garnish.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Stir, bringing to a boil.
Start timing at full boil, 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well, using only your hands.
Any other utensil is pretty much useless.
Pour onto a greased tray.
Chill at once.

title: chocolate bundles
directions: Thaw pastry 30 minutes.
Pre-heat oven to 425°.
On a lightly floured surface, roll pastry to a 12 inch square; cut into four 6 inch squares.
In the center of each square, place 1/4 c. chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon walnuts.
Bring pastry corners together just above the chocolate chips then twist and turn to seal.
Fan out the corners.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10-15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Melt cheeses together.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 can Ro-Tel tomatoes and chilies.
Add Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces (to taste).
Serve warm with Fritos or tostados.

title: sicilian steak
directions: Put olive oil on a dinner plate (big enough for steak).
On another plate, mix bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip steak in oil, covering both sides, then on to the bread crumbs, covering both sides. Broil for 10 min, then flip to cook other side.
Serve with Italian bread, butter and a salad.
Bon Apetit!

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend together sugar and flour.
Stir into eggs with remaining ingredients.
Turn into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ezekiel's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water and 1 tablespoon of honey. Set aside 10 minutes.
Combine the next 5 ingredients.
Blend lentils, oil, remaining honey and a small amount of water in a blender.
Place in a large mixing bowl with remaining water.
Stir in two cups of (mixed) flour.
Add the yeast mixture.
Stir in salt and remaining flour.
Place on floured bread board and knead until smooth.
Put in oiled bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk. Knead again.
Cut dough and shape into four large loaves.
Place in greased pans and let rise.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: avocado and tomato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over avocados and toss.
Stir in bacon, tomatoes and onion.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours (until very chilled).
Just before serving, spoon over salad greens with slotted spoon.
Serve immediately.

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Put in a baking dish.
Pour in milk, flour and sugar; stir real well.
Put in peaches.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in nuts; pour into pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, about 1 cup flour at a time, mixing after each addition.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add cream slowly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes.

title: better than sex cakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box. Stir in coconut and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 24 to 32 minutes.

When done, punch holes with wooden spoon. Combine sugar and pineapple; boil 10 minutes. Pour over cake and poke holes full of pineapple; cool. Mix pudding; let it set up. After cake is cool, ice with pudding, then with Cool Whip.
Garnish with candy sprinkles if desired.

title: cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together thoroughly.
Sift flour and salt together and stir in.
Mix with hands.
Press and mold into long, smooth roll, about 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice very thin with sharp knife.
