Cook at 325° until brown.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well and use on tossed salad.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Add tomato sauce and vegetables. Bring to a boil.
Then lower to simmer.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Place biscuits on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are browned.

title: pudding cake
directions: Combine the flour, butter and nuts.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly.
Mix together the cream cheese, xxx sugar and 1/2 carton of Cool Whip.
Spread evenly over the baked crust. Whip together the chocolate pudding and 1/2 the milk.
Spread over the cream cheese mixture.
Do the same with the vanilla pudding, spreading over the chocolate pudding.
Cover with the remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle some chopped nuts on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: texas mexican casserole
directions: Brown and salt meat and onion.
In a casserole dish, crumble 1/2 of chips.
Cover with meat mixture, then cover with liquid mixture (heat before pouring liquids).
Cover with grated cheese. Top with remaining crumbled chips.
Bake in open casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Delicious.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and cool.
Add carrots, green pepper and onion.
Mix together Eagle Brand milk, vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and pour over macaroni and vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli into bite sized pieces.
Mix all ingredients and marinate at least 1 hour.

title: swedish spice cake
directions: In a saucepan, mix together the first 4 ingredients, letting it barely come to a boil; remove from heat and cool.
Add the dry ingredients and mix.
Bake until done at 350° in a greased, lined bread pan.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: In large saucepan, cook rice without seasoning mix, according to package directions.
Reserve seasoning mix for later.
In large skillet, saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Set aside.

title: winter squash - beef stew
directions: Put meat in flour and brown with the onions.
Add water and seasonings.
Simmer for 50 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots and peas.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Add squash and tomato paste; continue cooking for another 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cut up fruit and nuts until fine. Pour cake mix over all and mix gently. Add flavoring and milk to beaten eggs. Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots and cook.
Chop onion and pepper.
Layer with carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over layered vegetables.
Bake at 375° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add sour cream, then melted chocolate. Blend in flour and baking powder which has been sifted together.
Add vanilla, then hot water with soda mixed into it.
The batter will be thin. Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels and nuts.

title: catherine's cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Boil cabbage.
Fry bacon and let stand. Saute onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in bacon grease.
Add cooked cabbage and 1/2 crumbled bacon to sauteed mixture.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cheese, seasoning and saute another 5 minutes.
Put in large casserole dish.
Top with remaining bacon and cheese.
Cover and heat for 30 minutes in 300° oven.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine oil, catsup, vinegar, sugar, onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt in a jar; shake vigorously.
Refrigerate.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix ingredients in a gallon jug. Fill jug up with water. Refrigerate. Serve icy cold.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Put into a casserole or baking dish.
Then drop cake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: communion bread
directions: Beat oil-water until frothy.
Mix with flour to form dough. Mix well and roll between wax paper.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with pastry wheel 1/2-inch square.
Prick each square.
Bake at 450° to 475° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Yields 250.

title: apple walnut syrup
directions: Melt butter; add nuts to brown slightly.
Remove nuts and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Remove cover and simmer 3 more minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts. Serve on waffles, pancakes, ice cream, custard, etc.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease casserole dish well.
Pour in corn.
Beat with fork the egg with the milk.
Pour into corn and mix.
Add cracker crumbs and mix.
Sprinkle more cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 240° for 1 hour.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Stir jello into boiling water until dissolved.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill until jelled.
Delicious!

title: kathy's meow
directions: Cook your macaroni; drain.
Chunk up pepperoni, cucumber and tomatoes.
Cut olives and onion to your desire.
Mix everything together; mix in your Italian dressing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Chill dough in refrigerator for one hour.
Roll into balls the size of large walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour; crisscross.
Bake until set but not hard.
Heat oven to 375°. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Place first three ingredients in top of double boiler and cook until cheese is melted.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased mold.
When set, unmold and serve with crackers.

title: belgian stewed leeks
directions: Wash leeks thoroughly and cut into chunks.
Cook in water. Add butter. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, until tender, adding a little water if necessary. The broth can be thickened by adding a little cornstarch, if desired.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites; mix oil and egg yolks.
Mix in other ingredients and fold in egg whites.
Bake in layers for 30 minutes at 350°.
When cake is cooled, place filling between layers.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together two times.
Add to the creamed mixture alternating with the milk.
Add vanilla.
Blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: nancie's easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch (approximately) Pyrex pan. Mix the other ingredients together and pour dough over butter. Pour 1 quart or large can of peaches over dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Saute ground meat in a stockpot over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, until no longer pink.
Add onion and continue to saute.
When onion is slightly brown, add bell pepper and celery.
Cook slightly.
Add all other ingredients, except spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours.
Allow to cool, then cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Skim off the fat that hardens on the surface.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Flake salmon; reserve juice.
Mix egg with salmon.
Then stir in flour or cornmeal.
Add baking powder to 1/4 cup of salmon juice.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Spoon drops into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: microwave mini omelet
directions: Place all ingredients in paper cups.
Cup should be about 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Beat all ingredients well.
Cook about 45 seconds. Remove from oven and stir well.
Top will be firm but underneath will be soft.
(Egg mixture will continue to cook out of the oven.)
If too soft, cook in 10 second segments until desired texture.
Eat right out of cup.
No dishes.
This is a great breakfast for children or people on the go.

title: hawaiian dream whip cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and beat at medium speed 4 minutes. Add juice from oranges and blend.
Tear orange slices apart and blend into batter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cool completely.

title: peach coffee cake
directions: Mix all together just until blended.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef pastichio(greek)
directions: Prepare macaroni per package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Stir flour into melted butter or margarine in heavy saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk and cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
Cover and cool.
Brown onion and ground beef in large frying pan.
Pour off drippings.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, cinnamon and oregano over beef.
Stir in tomato puree; cook slowly for 10 minutes.

title: mash potato candy
directions: Mix to make a stiff dough.
Roll out to a thin layer.
Spread with peanut butter or marshmallow cream, nuts, raisins or chocolate chips. Roll into a log shape. Slice into pieces.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until done.
Drain and rinse with cool water.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours before serving.

title: no-time-at-all stuffing loaf
directions: Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cook onion and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in poultry seasoning, sage and oregano; mix.
Remove from heat.
Add bread cubes, corn and nuts; mix.
Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, margarine and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing a little.
Add vegetable mixture; mix.
Spread into pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chop chop
directions: Bring to a boil.
Search refrigerator to find any leftover meats or gravies.
Slice chicken, skin and all, into small chunks. Add bouillon, if needed.
You can add any leftover hamburg or other meats.
Simmer all together.
Serve over rice.

title: orange sugar cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, 3/4 cup sugar, orange peel and vanilla until creamy.
Add egg product; beat for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in flour.
Mix until blended.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Shape dough into 42 (3/4-inch) balls; roll in remaining sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Wrap and store at room temperature for up to 4 days.
Makes 42.
Serving:
1 cookie.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Place in bowl and add enough Italian dressing to cover.
Cover and marinate overnight.
(Mix in Blue Cheese with mushrooms, if desired.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add next 5 ingredients in order. Pour into 8-inch pie plate with pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter taste cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and butter; add eggs one at a time.
Add additional ingredients except chips.
Pour into a jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread with peanut butter.
Refrigerate until cool.
Melt chips and spread over cake.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Dressing Mixture:
Mix sugar, canola oil, pepper, salt, vinegar and seasoning package (in Ramen noodles) to make dressing; set aside.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix in order given and pour in 15 x 10-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or golden brown and edges pull away from pan.
While warm, spread on top a glaze of:

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 12-cup tube pan.
Beat oleo and cream cheese together in mixing bowl until well blended.
Add sugar to mixture and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together; blend into creamed mixture.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, then use toothpick to test for doneness.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then turn out and cool completely.

title: chewy chocolate cake
directions: Mix oleo, water, oil and cocoa; bring to boil in a saucepan. Pour over flour and sugar and mix well.
Add baking soda to buttermilk; add to flour mixture and add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased oblong pan.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost while warm.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake as instructed.
Mix together Coco Lopez and Eagle Brand milk.
When cake is done, while hot, poke holes in it with a fork.
Pour mixture of Coco Lopez and milk over cake.
Let cool. Top with Cool Whip, then
sprinkle frozen coconut over the top.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening and eggs.
Add rest.
You can chill dough or roll in flour immediately to cook.
Bake at 375° for 10 or 11 minutes, until lightly browned around edges.
Cover with icing or roll in sugar and cinnamon before cooking.

title: quick and easy banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: instant salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and oranges.
Mix cottage cheese, pineapple, oranges and jellos.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: reuben snacks
directions: Spread each piece of party rye with mustard.
Top with 2 slices sausage, 1 teaspoon sauerkraut, 1 slice Swiss cheese and 1 dill slice.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Measure peanut butter and corn syrup into mixing bowl; mix until blended.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly and firmly in bottom and around sides of greased 9-inch pie pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread ice cream in chilled crust.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into wedges to serve; garnish with cherries or other fruit.
To remove pie pieces easily, place hot wet towel under bottom of pan or allow to stand a few minutes.

title: hershey chocolate pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars in microwave until softened.
Combine Cool Whip, candy bars and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into chocolate pie crust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix in large bowl, flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Gradually add sugar and oil, mixing well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Stir well and add zucchini and walnuts.

title: grandma falk's baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut up and cook in salted water until tender. Drain in colander.
Put in bowl and chop with knife.
Cook chopped onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add to eggplant. Next, add beaten egg yolk, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Place mixture in buttered baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla cookies with chocolate and coconut topping
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla extract in a bowl until you get a real smooth firm density.
Preheat oven to 350°. Make a half inch space between each cookie, then cook for 15 minutes and add sprinkles.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken, broth, soup and vegetables.
Spread evenly in a 7 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Mix flour, milk, and margarine.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° about 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: shepherd pie
directions: In skillet add hamburger, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Brown meat and drain.
Precook pie shell.
Make packaged gravy.
Once gravy is done, add hamburger mixture to it.
In a cool pie shell add hamburger mixture then put frozen peas and top with mashed potatoes.
Heat in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can also put slices of American cheese on top.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems, brush caps with melted butter and place hollow-side up in pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken liver stroganoff
directions: Cut chicken livers into bite size pieces and fry in butter along with the onion until done.
Stir in sour cream and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve with rice, creamed potatoes or noodles.

title: request green beans
directions: Put alternate layers of drained beans and onions in a casserole.
Mix soup with the bean liquid and almonds (or water chestnuts); pour over beans and onions.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick sweet and sour chix wings
directions: Marinate 24 hours.
Cook wings in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Turn every half hour.

title: aunt rebecca's artichoke dip
directions: Put all ingredients into a food processor.
Process for a few minutes, until well blended.
Put into an ovenproof or microwave-proof dish and heat for
a few minutes.
It's best heated just before serving.
Crackers or chunks of sourdough bread are good with this dip.

title: blue cheese grilled bread
directions: In a
small
bowl
combine
butter,
Blue cheese, green onion and garlic
powder.
Spread on one side of each slice of bread. Toast slices
on
grill
over hot coals 3 to 4 minutes until golden brown,
turning over after 2 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: silver white cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat flour, sugar, milk, shortening and vanilla on low speed for 30 seconds, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Beat in egg whites on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan (2 round or 1 sheet pan).
Bake layers for 30 to 35 minutes or sheet cake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: ruby's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except sherbet. Chill. When ready to serve it, pour into punch bowl and add sherbet. Serves 15 people.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam zucchini and onion for 5 minutes.
Mix carrots, sour cream and soup and stir in zucchini mixture.
Prepare stuffing mix using only 3/4 cup water and 1/2 cup margarine.
Layer in a 3-quart casserole half of the stuffing, then the zucchini mixture and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: gram's banana bread
directions: Beat together Crisco, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, bananas and soda, then add flour.
Put in greased tin and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: toasted noodle cakes
directions: Bring water to a boil; add noodles and salt.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 2 minutes.
Rinse under cold water and drain.
Mix noodles with 2 tablespoons oil.
Heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Add noodles; spread to cover bottom of pan.
On medium heat, brown noodles on underside; turn and brown other side.
Remove from skillet and cut into 6 servings.

title: reese cups
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add
peanut butter and powdered sugar; mix well.
Take mixture and spread into a 10 x 15-inch pan. Melt Hershey bar over low heat and spread over mixture.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: beefy onion pretzels
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine and add soup mix.
Break up pretzels and add to mixture. Mix well, coating all pretzels. Spread on cookie sheet and bake in oven set at 350° for 5 minutes. Stir pretzels on sheet and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Cool and enjoy!

title: southern baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil in skillet. Place in a shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the chops.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: no fat cake
directions: Mix above ingredients. Put in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date-applesauce loaf
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar. Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Measure out 1/4 cup and reserve. Add remaining flour mixture alternating with applesauce to the creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Toss reserved flour mixture with nuts and dates.
Fold into the batter, mixing well.
Turn into greased and floured pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Frost with chocolate icing or use cream cheese mixed with orange marmalade.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Fry meats together.
Drain well.
Add cheese to meat and simmer until cheese melts.
Serve on rye bread.
Sandwiches can be fixed and kept frozen to be used later.
Just heat in oven and serve.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in casserole dish and top with butter. Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: old fashioned wassail(beverage; serves 20 to 30)
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add the tea, juice and juice of lemons to water and sugar after they boil.
Make pouch out of coffee filter or thin handkerchief to steep the spices (ginger, cinnamon and cloves).
Remove after 1/2 hour.
Add to everything for 1/2 hour.
Remove.
Can be made several days ahead, but heat to steaming before serving.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix dry ingredients and cut in margarine with 2 knives or a pastry blender.
Stir in milk.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 12.
Can be used for dumplings too.

title: popcorn pudding
directions: Mix and bake 1/2 hour.
Serve warm.

title: best candy apple ever
directions: Melt baking chocolate on low in microwave, stirring constantly.
Dip each apple in melted chocolate and cool completely on wax paper.
Melt caramels on low in microwave, stirring constantly.
You may have to add a little corn syrup to be able to stir the melted caramels.
Dip each cool chocolate apple in the caramel, then sprinkle with chopped almonds.
Serve when cool.

title: turnip greens
directions: Wash greens real good, maybe 4 times.
Chop greens into bite-size pieces.
Put greens in water.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar, salt, pepper and salt pork.
Bring to a brisk boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl that has a tight fitting lid. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Stir lightly so the dressings marinate evenly.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients (only 1 1/3 cups crushed chips) together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sour cream, extra cheese and 1 cup remaining crushed chips.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spiced holiday pecans
directions: Melt butter and add seasonings.
Mix thoroughly. Add pecans and toss gently until all nuts are coated.
Place in shallow baking pan. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Turn at least once. Yields 4 cups pecans.

title: christmas tea
directions: Fill mug with water.
Drop in candy.
Microwave until hot enough to melt patties.
Add cinnamon, stir and enjoy.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Drain pineapple completely and reserve juice.
Set pineapple aside.

title: blueberry muffins with lemon
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix with fork the beaten egg, milk and butter.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix 1st 7 ingredients.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk. Sift cocoa, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to eggs mixture.
Add zucchini.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain fat.
Add the next 6 ingredients to the meat; simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook the lasagne in boiling water; rinse in cold water.

Mix together the remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella. Form layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan, starting with half of the lasagne, then 1/2 the cottage cheese mixture, then 1/2 the meat mixture, then 1/2 the Mozzarella.
Repeat layers with remainder, then place in oven.
Bake at 375°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Beat.
Add bananas, flour and soda.
Beat until smooth. Add vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 3 mini loaves or 2 regular loaves.

title: why not salad
directions: Bring crushed pineapple with juice to a boil and add jello, buttermilk, coconut and pecans.
When cool, fold in Cool Whip.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: *I use a Salad Shooter to crumble the crackers.

title: fudge
directions: Boil all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Beat with a wooden spoon until thick.
Pour into a large dish and let cool.

title: brandy slush
directions: In a large saucepan or kettle, heat 7 cups of the water.
Stir in sugar.
Set aside to cool.

title: creamy orange fruit salad
directions: Mix fruits in large bowl and set aside.
In a small bowl mix pudding, milk and orange juice for 2 minutes.
Add sour cream, mix well.
Spoon over fruit.
Toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Makes 8-10 servings.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add whipped cream, mayonnaise, marshmallows, chopped nuts and cherries with well drained pineapple.
Can be frozen and thawed out an hour or so before serving.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Place chicken in center of a piece of foil.
Top with chopped vegetables and all other ingredients.
Wrap well.
Place on baking sheet; cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini-carrot bread or muffins
directions: Into large bowl, sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
In medium bowl, beat eggs and oil; stir in sugar and vanilla.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients; add zucchini and carrots and stir just until completely blended.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute celery, pepper and mushrooms in oil for 3 to 4 minutes. Add undiluted condensed soups and bring to a simmer.
Add chicken and pimento. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and simmer for 5 minutes. Serve over biscuits or toast.
Serves 4.

title: apple-nut chess pie
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and lemon juice, mixing with wire whisk until well blended.
Add eggs and margarine; mix well.
Stir in combined apples, sugar, nuts and flour.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°, continuing to bake for 45 minutes or until top is firm.

title: red beans and rice with beef sausage
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Add water, bring to a boil and immediately turn off stove.
Let beans sit for 1 hour.
Do not lift lid.
Pour off water and replace with fresh hot water.
Add all ingredients and simmer approximately 2 hours or until beans are tender and broth is fairly thick.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: quick fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave bowl.
Heat on medium-high, stirring frequently, until everything is melted together.
Spread in 9 x 9-inch buttered (not greased) pan.
Chill in refrigerator until very firm.

title: holiday lime punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, pour ginger ale, then add the cream, then the sherbet.
Stir down foam periodically.

title: mexican-chicken casserole
directions: Combine cream of mushroom and chicken soup, chicken broth, onion, celery, bell pepper, tomatoes and chilies, 1 cup cheese, chicken, salt and pepper.
Line greased 3-quart baking dish with tortilla chips.
Pour mixture over chips.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until cheese is bubbly but not brown.
Perfect for potluck dinners.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and the eggs.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon; roll balls in mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Immediately remove from baking sheet.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Melt Kool-Aid in 1 cup warm water.
Add other 3 1/2 cups and other ingredients.
Freeze.

title: french onion soup
directions: Using large pan, saute onions in butter until golden brown and tender.
Add beef stock, Worcestershire sauce and a dash of pepper.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Put into blender or mixer and beat until smooth. Place bread in bottom of bowl.
Pour heated cheese mixture over bread.
Serve hot and garnish with chopped green onions.

title: fruited cream cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy.
Add sour cream, strawberry preserves, lemon rind and juice, mixing until light and fluffy.
Spoon into serving dish and garnish with a strawberry fan, if desired.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: apple muffins recipe(12 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Measure out flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Put into sifter.
Sift these together into a bowl.
Measure out milk and oil. Add these to the flour mixture. Break egg into small bowl.
Peel and chop apple.
Add egg and apple to other ingredients.
Grease muffin tins; fill tins 2/3 full of batter.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: orange fruit juice
directions: Get any color bowl.
Slice the orange and put it in the bowl. Put orange juice in, then pineapple juice, then ginger ale.
Stir it up.
Put it in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours.
Then take it out; pour in a cup and drink it!

title: wild blueberry maple syrup muffins
directions: Preheat oven 350°; grease muffin tin and set aside. Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt.
Mix together oil, beaten egg, milk, syrup and oats.
Stir into dry mixture until moistened; do not overmix.
Fold in floured blueberries; fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full and sprinkle tops with a little granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and soda, alternately with milk.
Fold in vanilla and egg whites.
Add coconut and nuts last, leaving a small amount of each for icing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: timmy's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix 1/2 cup melted butter, peanut butter, powdered sugar and crushed grahams.
Spread into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 6 ounces butter and chocolate chips together, then spread on top and chill until firm.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pineapple juice, egg and vinegar in a saucepan.
Simmer to thicken.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip to the thickened mixture and mix well.
Add apples and half of the peanuts (if necessary you may need to add another apple).
Put in serving bowl and top with remaining peanuts.
Chill, serve and enjoy!

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix cabbage and salmon broken up into small pieces together. Add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Serve with soda crackers.
Will serve 2 to 3 people.
Great for lunch, served with a drink, a meal in itself.

title: macaroni dinner
directions: Cook macaroni; drain (save 1 cup of juice).
Mix soup, onion, pimento, mayonnaise and 1/2 cup of juice.
Layer macaroni, mixture, cheese, macaroni and rest of mixture.
Pour remainder of juice. Top with remainder of the cheese.

title: filling balls
directions: Mix together ingredients and make balls; place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil until last 10 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish; set aside, then mix sugar, flour, baking powder and sweet milk.
Pour into melted butter dish.
Add pie filling.
Don't stir, just gently move pie filling into flour mix from side to side, very gently, and bake at 350° until brown. I use glass baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Serves 6.

title: plain sugar cookies(cut out very nice)
directions: Measure flour; add baking powder and salt and sift again. Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add vanilla and flour alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Chill overnight.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes or until done.
Yields 6 dozen medium size cookies.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix
zucchini, onion,
Bisquick
and
cheese
together. Beat eggs.
Add oil, then
add this to zucchini mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan
and bake at 350° (325° if glass) for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking; cover with crushed potato chips if desired. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: little meat pies
directions: Combine shortening and flour in a large Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until roux is caramel colored. Add pork, beef, onion, parsley and seasonings; cook over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain and cool.

title: cranberry-apple sweet potatoes
directions: Spread pie filling in 8 x 8-inch baking dish; arrange sweet potatoes on top.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together cranberry sauce, apricot preserves and orange marmalade.
Spoon over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Nutrition info per serving:
354 calories, 83 gr carbo, 2 gr fat, 0 mg chol, 29 mg sodium.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil and water.
Add liquid to the cake mix and Jell-O.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into oiled, large flat pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Mix garlic, olive oil, soy sauce and tomato paste.
Spread over London broil.
After marinating for several hours, cook as desired.

title: italian cream cake(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; cream and add egg yolks.
Mix soda and buttermilk together and add to other ingredients with flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend well and fold in coconut and nuts.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Best cooked in 3 layers, but can be packed in large two layers or large Bundt pan.
Depending on size of pans, bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash rice in sieve.
Put in pan and cook until done (about 15 minutes).
Stir in milk, cinnamon, vanilla and butter.
Put in baking dish and bake 2 hours.
Stir 4 times the first hour.
Do not stir 2nd hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Put eggs in a bowl.
Beat with a fork.
Add a little salt and flour (continue adding flour until you can handle easily).
Then roll out.
Add flour, roll out and turn over until dough is real thin.
Let dry for 30 minutes to one hour.
Roll up dough and cut into small noodles.

title: sauerkraut surprise cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs; add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa powder.
Add to cream mixture, alternating with water. Stir in sauerkraut.
Pour into a floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients, then add flour and oats.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator at least 30 minutes.
Spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs together, add sugar.
Stir 1 teaspoon soda into molasses and 1 teaspoon soda into milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured large oblong pan.
Bake in medium oven for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix beans, soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onions in a bowl.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops; place in baking pan.
Put cut up potatoes around chops.
Add chopped onion.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid (any flavor) according to package directions. Stir in juice and place in freezer.
Stir 1 time each hour for 6 hours.
Delicious!

title: grits souffle
directions: Bring salted water to a rolling boil and slowly stir in grits. Cook until thick (about 3 minutes), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine and garlic cheese until melted. Put eggs in cup; beat well, then add milk to make 1 cup.
Add to grits mixture.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: glaze for quick breads or bar cookies or sweet rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put on baked goods while it is still hot and return to the oven for two or three minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Fit one pie crust into a 9 inch pie pan; flute edge.

title: best ever cole slaw
directions: Stir sugar, salt and pepper into milk.
Let stand 5 minutes, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add vinegar, slowly, stirring to keep smooth.
Pour over cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Mix until well coated with dressing.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Then cook cheese, flour, milk and margarine in another pan, stirring constantly.
When thick, add to macaroni and mix well.
Serve hot.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Roll vanilla wafers into fine crumbs. Add melted margarine. Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put in refrigerator to set.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix pudding with undrained pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in nuts and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until firm. This can be made ahead and frozen.

title: rosemary-lemon shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line 9 x 9 x 2-inch square baking pan with aluminum foil.
Coat with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and make into small balls.
Mix the chili sauce and jelly in baking dish. Drop meat balls in mixture and bake 45 minutes
You can make these, bake them and then freeze them.
Reheat when you want to use them.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: I put half plain and half Mexican.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put rice into baking pan with chicken on top.
Then put onion soup mix on chicken and cream of mushroom soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix green beans, peas, vegetables, water chestnuts, celery, onions, green peppers and pimento and chill.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
This makes dressing.
Mix well and pour over chilled vegetables.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Simmer soup bones in water for about 2 hours.
Add beef and all other ingredients to pan.
(Use all 12 to 14 ounce cans vegetables and the juices of all.)
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Best if simmered 3 to 4 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar together (no heat).
Mix with egg thoroughly.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Remove from heat.
Layer wafers, bananas, wafers, sauce, bananas, wafers, sauce, etc.

title: grouse on the grill
directions: Split birds in half along the keel bone.
When the coals are ready, place the unseasoned birds on the grill.
(I like medium hot coals, like you might grill chicken over.) Turn the halves frequently so they don't burn.
Meanwhile, put the rest of the ingredients in a saucepan.
Crush the garlic clove first.
Put the pan on one side of the grill, melting the butter and blending everything.
Stir this, the basting sauce, every now and then. When the birds are browning nicely, begin basting, first one side and then the other.
When you think they're done, they probably are.
Not having as much fat, grouse don't take as much cooking as chicken.
A bit of salt to taste and the birds can be served.

title: italian beef
directions: Trim fat and cube roast.
Place in crock-pot.
Slice small amount garlic; chop onion and add to beef.
Add seasonings and water; stir.
Cook in cook pot overnight.
Stir occasionally. Serve on sliced steak buns and sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese.

title: mom's best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray. In a medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well. In a large bowl, whisk together egg whites, egg, sugar, applesauce, oil and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture until just blended.
Pour batter into pan and sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake for about 25 minutes and let cool for 15 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Heat bacon drippings over medium heat; add flour slowly and stir constantly until roux is a chocolate brown.
This takes a long time.
Add celery, onions, green pepper, garlic and parsley and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Fry okra in shortening until slightly browned.
Add to first mixture and stir well for a few minutes.
Add chicken stock, water, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, catsup, tomatoes with juice, salt, ham, bay leaves, thyme and rosemary.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add chicken, crabmeat and shrimp and simmer 30 minutes more.
Add brown sugar and lemon juice.
Serve in bowls over hot rice.
Serves 20.

title: chicken with summac(mousakhan)
directions: Draw, singe, cut in halves and wash chicken.
Drain.
Rub chicken inside-out with the seasoning.
Mix the summac, some salt and chopped onions well.
Add olive oil to the mixture.
In a baking tray, pour some olive oil.
Split the loaves of bread into two and place in the tray.
Spoon some onion mixture into the center of each loaf.
Place half the chicken on top of each mound of onion mixture.
Place a mound of onion and summac on top of each chicken.
Cover chicken with the remaining split bread.
Pour remaining oil and summac over bread.
Bake in a hot oven for 1 hour.
Sprinkle water over bread and if bread begins to brown, cover with aluminum foil.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jam bars
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves in a large bowl. Beat at low speed until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups of mixture; press remaining onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla; add pineapple.
Set aside.
Crush graham crackers and mix with oleo.
Spread in bottom and sides of cake pan.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil onion and potatoes in water for 20 minutes or until tender.
Add celery and California Blend vegetables and boil 15 minutes more.
Add soup and Velveeta.
Simmer until cheese melts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to boil, stirring
5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla. Pour over popped corn and mix together to coat all corn. Put on jelly roll pans. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: gale's microwaved pecans
directions: Place pecans in microwavable dish. Add butter and salt, mix well. Microwave on high for 1 1/2 minutes, remove and stir. Microwave another 1 1/2 minutes, stir and check for desired doneness.

title: quick and easy beer cheese soup
directions: Combine
all ingredients in saucepan and heat thoroughly.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter and boil 1 minute.
Pour over oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper and cool.

title: date nut roll
directions: Cut and soak dates overnight.
Stew until soft.
Add rest of ingredients to make consistency of pumpkin pie.
Pour in crust; add broken or cut nuts (pecans).
Bake at 350° until firm, about 1/2 hour.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar and butter until fluffy.
Stir in Bisquick and pecans until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of the mixture.
Press remainder in baking pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese and white sugar.
Beat in remainder of ingredients until smooth and spread over cooked bottom.
Sprinkle with rest of crumbs.
Bake until center is firm, approximately 25 minutes.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine. Add sugar. Cream well. Add eggs 1 at a time. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture with mashed bananas, milk, vanilla and nuts. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat the egg and add water to make 3/4 c. liquid, add vinegar and baking pwd. to egg mixture, stir into flour and shortening mixture.
Refrigerate for 30 min. before rolling out.
This is excellent and can be worked over and over.
Also if not all used, it can be wrapped and frozen for later use.
Enjoy.
Makes 2 double pies.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Beat sugars and shortening thoroughly until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and beat until well blended.
Add pecans.
Make into rolls with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar, mixing until well blended.
Blend (one bowl) in 1 egg.
Melt margarine with chocolate over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add (2nd bowl) remaining sugar, eggs and vanilla to chocolate mixture.
Mix well. Add flour; mix.
Add nuts.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt jane's caramel icing
directions: Mix together well.
Let boil slowly.
Set pan in cold water, adding one teaspoon vanilla.
Stir until thick and spread on cake.

title: spinach and feta cheese pie
directions: Pass spinach through cheesecloth and remove all water.
In a large bowl, crumble Feta cheese and add beaten eggs.
Add spinach; mix very well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and place 10 pieces of filo into pan, brushing each piece with butter.
Spread spinach mixture evenly across filo and place 10 more pieces of filo over mixture.
Paint top with butter and egg wash and place in a 350° oven for about 3/4 hour, or until golden brown.
Cut in squares and serve hot or cold.
